title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onions and bacon and set aside.
Combine celery soup, potato soup, milk, clam juice and clams.
Add crumbled bacon and onions.
Heat and serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Sift sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Into pan, add milk; bring to a boil (slowly).
Cook 2 minutes.
Separate egg whites and yolks; save whites for meringue.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Keep alternating hot mixture into egg yolks. Stir into hot mixture.
Cook another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter.
Alternate mixture with wafers and bananas.
Top with meringue.
Double for larger pudding.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix drained hominy, onion, soup, margarine and Cheez Whiz. Place in casserole dish and cover with crushed Fritos.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thick sliced Irish potatoes in casserole dish.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Add 1 can water to can of chicken soup; pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(May add leftover ham, chicken or cheese.)

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal and oleo.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 11 x 15-inch pan. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oysters a la michael
directions: Mix catsup, Worcestershire and hot sauce in a bowl and set aside.
Fry bacon until brown but not crispy.
Spoon 1 tablespoon sauce into each shell.
Wrap each oyster with a piece of cooked bacon.
Place wrapped oyster in shell in center of sauce and top with additional sauce.
Bake for 5 minutes at 450°.
Remove from oven and top each with grated cheese.
Return to oven and broil until cheese melts (about 2 to 3 minutes).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cook broccoli for 5 minutes. Cool, stem and chop. Mix with all other ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodle as directed on box and drain.
Mix tuna, soup and milk in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in noodles.
Crush potato chips and put over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mystery salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and chill.
Serve with sour cream with salt and horseradish added to taste.

title: strawberry cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Do not overmix. Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly. Cool right side up in pan for about 25 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Mix wet ingredients into dry ingredients just enough to combine. Mixture will be lumpy.
Fold in 1 can drained blueberries.
Bake in 12 greased muffin pans at 400°, between 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat peach pie
directions: Line dish with a layer of graham crackers. Put peaches on top of graham crackers and top the peaches with another layer of graham crackers. Mix pudding according to directions on package. Place pudding on top of graham crackers and top pudding with Lite Cool Whip. Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peanut brittle # 1
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in a frying pan.
Have frying pan on high.
Bring to a boil.
Add peanuts and cook for 10 minutes. Add vanilla and stir in baking soda.
Pour into greased pan.
Let harden and break into pieces.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Whip the cream until stiff, not dry.
Fold cream into cheese mixture.
Spread in pastry shell.
Stir lemon juice into pie filling.
Spoon over cream filling.
Chill.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook together for 3 minutes the margarine, water, dried onions and broccoli.
Remove from heat and add Minute rice, cream of celery soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well and put into a large casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
(If you are in a hurry like I am, just cook it all on the stove.)

title: christmas hot punch
directions: Mix juices (using equal parts, I use quart size cans) and tea in large pan.
Pour in red hots.
Heat until red hots have melted. Pour mixture into a crock-pot to keep warm.
May be served hot or cold.
May use frozen juices.

title: applesauce walnut cake and frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans.
Put dry cake mix, butter, applesauce, eggs and cinnamon into large mixing bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in black walnuts.
Turn batter into pans and spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy biscuit tortoni
directions: Place 2 fluted paper baking cups in each of 12 muffin pan cups. Soften ice cream. Whirl macaroons in blender until crumbs form or pull apart with fingers to form crumbs. Add 2/3 cup macaroon crumbs, 1/2 cup whipped topping, cherries and almond extract to softened ice cream. Spoon tortoni mixture into cups. Sprinkle tops with remaining crumbs. Decorate with whipped topping. Freeze until firm.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Saute the meat in butter in skillet until nicely browned. Cook the noodles in boiling water.
Drain.
Add meat, vegetables and tomatoes.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: crab imperial
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Combine crab, celery, pimento and wine.
Toss with shells.
Place in 3 quart baking dish.
Blend mayonnaise, half and half, and seasonings.
Pour over shells. Garnish with buttered crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 one cup servings.

title: quick-as-a-wink rolls
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add egg and water, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
May store batter, tightly covered, in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: ho - ho cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, but bake in greased jelly roll pan for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wild chili
directions: Brown each type of meat with one onion and one pepper.
Place each batch of meat in colander and rinse under warm water.
Put browned meat in large stew pot.
Add juice and two packages of seasoning.
Squeeze stewed tomatoes into bits; add to pot along with juice.
Add Ro-Tel.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add more chili powder to taste.
Simmer 2 more hours.
Do not add beans.
Serve with shredded cheese, chopped onions, crackers, Fritos.
Can be frozen in small batches; great for groups.

title: german beer cheese
directions: Mix together all ingredients except beer.
Add enough beer to spreading consistency.
Pack tightly into a bowl or mold.
Chill several hours.
Unmold and serve at room temperature.

title: rolled meat loaf with cheese(serves 6)
directions: Beat egg.
Add to beef and pork and mix thoroughly.
Add 1/2 of tomato sauce, onions, crackers and spices.

title: "party" chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken wings in salty cold water.
Drain thoroughly. Place chicken wings in glass baking dish.
Mix sauce, juice and garlic together and pour over chicken wings.
Soak overnight (24 hours).

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat together sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Melt together 1/2 cup milk and 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs, beat after each addition. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add grated carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix cheese and condensed milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust.
Chill 3 hours. Top with cherry filling.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients. Set a 1 1/2-quart baking dish in shallow pan on oven rack. Pour water to 1-inch depth around dish. Pour pudding in baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in pudding comes out clean. Yield: 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a
large bowl, break the eggs, beat slightly with a fork. Add
meat
and
toss
lightly.
Mix
onion,
pepper and crumbs, add
to
meat mixture and mix lightly.
Add the salt, mustard, milk
and ketchup.
Add horseradish, mix lightly but well.
Bake at
in
a
greased loaf pan for 40 minutes. Spread
top of loaf with 1/2 cup ketchup if you like.
(Mixing lightly keeps loaf from being tough.)

title: mozzarella and tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes and arrange on plate.
Trickle olive oil over tomatoes and sprinkle with black pepper.
Lay slices of cheese over tomatoes and strip of basil over cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.

title: multi grain pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Grease a 14-inch pizza pan.
Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Press onto pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Top with remaining ingredients and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; cook until temperature reaches 290°, stirring constantly.
Cook until golden brown.
Pour onto cookie sheet; spread.
As it cools, use paper towels to soak up grease.
Melt the chocolate chips; spread over top.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: brownies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl, cream butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Pour dry ingredients into creamed butter mixture.
Mix for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (will be very thick).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After 15 minutes, watch closely.

title: raisin crumb pie
directions: Cook raisins with sugar (1/2 cup).
Cover with water, 1 1/2 cups sugar, shortening and flour.
Crumb these together.
Save 1 cup crumbs for top of pie.
Add to balance of crumbs the eggs, baking powder and milk.
Line two 8-inch pie pans with pastry. Add cooked raisins with juice.
Pour batter over raisins and cover with crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: strawberry bread with spread
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup strawberry juice for spread.
Mix all dry ingredients together in large mixer bowl.
Make a hole in the center of the mixture.
Pour strawberries, oil and eggs in the hole.
Mix by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly combined. Stir in nuts.
Pour into two waxed paper lined loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Beat eggs with milk; add shortening and corn and combine.
Mix lightly.
Drop from teaspoon into fat heated to 365°.
Fry until brown and cooked in center, 4 to 5 minutes; drain.
Makes 8 fritters.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat and add other ingredients. Simmer until vegetables are tender, and enjoy.

title: ernie's italian beef
directions: Sprinkle beef roast with garlic salt, pepper and oregano. Roast to medium as usual.
Chill.
Slice and reserve drippings. To drippings, add remaining ingredients, including sliced beef. Simmer, covered, until beef is fully cooked.
May need to add water while cooking.
Serve hot on Italian rolls, or Italian bread (cut in 3 to 4 pieces and sliced almost all the way through, like a hot dog bun).

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Mix well together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk. In a separate bowl, mix both flours and salt.
Add to creamy mixture and mix well.
Then add flavoring and pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Mix rice, cream soups and water and place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Lay clean pieces of chicken on top and spread dry soup mix over all.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6. It's also good using pork chops.

title: southern coconut pie
directions: Scald milk and butter.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt, then add to milk mixture.
Mix well.
Add coconut, mix well and pour into unbaked pie crust.

title: pork chop slop
directions: Cook stuffing according to directions on box.
Place cooked stuffing in casserole dish.
Layer pork chops over stuffing.
Pour gravy over pork chops.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cocoa cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add butter and milk.
Put on stove and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla, rolled oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with nonstick vegetable spray and dust with flour.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, blend 3/4 cup flour, 1/4 cup of the sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and orange zest.
Set aside.

title: tandy takes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Blend in flour and baking powder; set aside.
Heat milk and butter until hot. Slowly pour into batter until blended. Batter will be thin. Pour into greased rimmed cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes or until cake bounces back to touch.
Spread peanut butter on hot cake.
Let cool in refrigerator about 1 hour or until firm. Melt 8-ounces milk chocolate in double boiler, then spread on top of peanut butter.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine oil, corn, cornmeal, onion, buttermilk, eggs, chopped peppers and 1 cup cheese.
Put in greased, hot, large iron skillet and sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot and celery stir-fry
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a large skillet for 2 minutes. Add carrots; saute 2 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add celery; saute 1 minute. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lower heat, cover and cook for 3 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: Make white sauce using first 3 ingredients.
Cool.
Add and blend egg, mustard, pepper, Old Bay, celery salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.
Gently add crabmeat.
Fill serving shells.

title: mom's economy soup
directions: Peel potatoes and onions.
Cube potatoes and chop onions into cooking pan, add rice.
Cover with water and cook until done.
Add tomato juice, margarine and salt.
Simmer until juice is cooked into the broth well.
If desired, additional vegetables may be added.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Blend butter into mixture.
Press firmly against sides and bottom of greased glass pie plate.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges brown slightly.
Yields one 8 to 9-inch pie crust.

title: lo-cal frosty cocoa and fruit yogurt smoothie
directions: Blend cocoa
and
milk	in blender.
Add yogurt and ice cubes until desired thickness.

title: crock pot stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in frying pan.
Put all ingredients into crock pot except cream cheese.
Add cream cheese 10 minutes before serving, make sure it melts and stir into rest of mixture.
Serve over noodles.
Cook in crock pot on low for 7 to 9 hours. 2 lbs. of skinless boneless chicken breast cubed can be substituted.

title: date balls(cookies)
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients over low heat until butter is melted. Add beaten egg and dates and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly, and cool.
Add pecans and cereal.
Form balls 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in coconut.

title: grilled steak wraps with spicy peanuts
directions: Heat grill to high. Pulse peanuts in a food processor until coarsely chopped; set aside. Heat olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat; add peanuts and cook, stirring often until fragrant, 3 minutes. Add fish or soy sauce, lime juice, peanut butter, scallions and ground red pepper. Cook, stirring constantly until wilted, 2 minutes; transfer mixture to a serving bowl. Sprinkle steak with salt and freshly ground pepper. Grill, turning once, 3 minutes for a medium-rare skirt steak; 6 minutes for a medium-rare flank steak. Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into thin slices. Serve sliced steak and peanut sauce wrapped in lettuce leaves and with the accompaniments of your choice.

title: hot chicken souffle
directions: Cube 2 slices bread in 9-inch square dish.
Mix together chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise and seasonings.	Spoon evenly over bread.
Put 4 slices cubed bread over mixture.
Mix egg and milk.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pour soup over casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour, 15 minutes.	Ten minutes before done, sprinkle cheese over top.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put all ingredients in punch bowl in order listed.
Keep repeating layers. Top with nuts. Refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook until firm balls form with stick in cold water (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and add 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Dampen hands with cold water and form balls.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumber slices.
Add sliced onions and shredded peppers. Mix with salt in center, bury a quart of chopped cucumbers. Cover with plate and wait.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer.
Do not boil!

title: banana bars
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and sour cream.
Then add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Reserve 1/2 cup with the soda, then stir in bananas (mashed) and salt.
Mix reserved flour with raisins, nuts and coconut.
Mix in butter and pour in jelly roll tin or cookie sheet, greased.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting, flavored with maple flavoring.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pasta, shrimp or tuna, pepper, carrots and zucchini.
Add Worcestershire, mayo, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to combine.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn
and string beans;
mix all ingredients in a large bowl.

title: breakfast biscuit delight
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Scramble eggs.
Cook sausage until done. Grate cheese.
Set aside all three.

title: spicy-orange-honey butter
directions: Beat all ingredients until fluffy.

title: icebox cucumbers
directions: Thinly slice 7 cups cucumbers.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt; cover and set aside for 1 hour.
Add vinegar, sugar and celery salt.
Add onion and pepper to cucumbers.
Pour over cucumbers. Place in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 4 weeks.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and use.

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in water; allow to cool.
Heat grease.
Slowly pour lye into grease.
Stir until the mixture drips from stirrer like strained honey.
Do not stir too long or it will separate, 5 to 10 minutes is about right.
Pour mixture into molds or pans. Cover with a heavy blanket and leave for 2 days.
Now, cut your snow white bars of soap into the desired size.

title: caramel squares
directions: Combine caramels with 1/2 evaporated milk. Melt in microwave or double boiler. Combine cake mix with the other 1/2 evaporated milk and butter. Stir in nuts. Press 1/2 of the mixture in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and drizzle with caramel. Crumble remaining cake mixture on top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool!
Lightly spoon 2 cans blueberry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Chill! Top with Cool Whip. Best if chilled overnight.
Cut into squares.
Serves 24.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine bananas, salt and soda.
Add sugar; mix.
Add butter and flour.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add cherries, egg and salad oil.
Mix well.
This will take about 5 minutes, until sugar dissolves. Place in an 8-inch square baking pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Let set overnight. Roll in nuts and serve with favorite crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell; set aside.
Mix the first 3 ingredients, then add small amount of milk to moisten.
Add egg yolks; stir.
Add rest of milk.
Cook until thick (stirring constantly).
Add butter and vanilla.
Place in baked pie shell; cover with beaten egg whites.
Place in a 375° oven until egg whites are light brown.

title: all american barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together until done.
Drain. Combine all ingredients into beef and onion.
Heat thoroughly. Makes 18 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook carrots in about 1/2-inch boiling water for about 6 minutes; drain.
Place carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish, combine all 8 of the other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Turn chicken at least once during cooking.
Sauce may be served over rice.
Serves 6.

title: aunt betty's corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and pour in casserole dish.
Top with corn bread mix.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
While still warm, prick with a fork all over and then put your icing on.

title: buckner's pralines
directions: Mix sugars in heavy pan.
Add Karo, milk and salt.
Stir in butter until melted.
Add pecans.
Place pan in cold water and stir until mixture begins to lose gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered foil.
Let harden, then they are ready to eat.
Easy, foolproof and wonderful!

title: spicy pumpkin pancakes
directions: Heat griddle or skillet and grease, if necessary. Stir all ingredients until blended. Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle. Cook until edges are dry. Turn and cook until golden brown. Makes about 18 pancakes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Knead the ingredients together as you would pie crust.
When it forms a ball, divide it into 4 patties.
Press into four 9-inch cake pans.
Prick all over with a fork, both ways. Bake in a 275° oven for about 1 hour or until a light delicate brown.

title: ham and cheese strata(serves 24)
directions: Grease a large, rectangular pan.
Cover bottom with bread. Pour 1/2 ham and 1/2 sauce over layer.
Keep layering.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine ingredients; mix until well blended.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths. Cut onion into eighths.
Chop onions.
Add garlic and oleo.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Puree soup in food processor or blender. Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg to soup.

title: grandma longwell cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate dough for at least 1 hour.
Roll out thick on a minimum amount of flour.
Do not overbake for soft cookies.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; mix sugar (NutrSweet), oil, nuts, eggs and zucchini.
Put in tube or loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until done.
(I used no icing, but topping could be used.)

title: mooncakes
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until it is very smooth.
Add the egg and beat just a little.
Add flour and flavoring.
Knead or pull and mash the dough with your hands until it is smooth.

title: chop suey
directions: Dice onions and celery; fry with hamburger until browned and mixed well in a large frypan.
In a large deep pan, cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Add tomato sauce, meat, onion and celery. Add water or more tomato sauce to make soupy.
Cook, the longer the better.
Before serving, add a large handful of spaghetti noodles to soak up liquid.
When ready, serve with warmed chow mein noodles and hot bread.

title: party punch
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Prepare lemonade according to directions, mix and add juice.
Before serving, add ice and ginger ale.
Good with rum or vodka added. Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: microwave play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place, uncovered, in microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.

title: low-fat orange bran muffins*
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, bran, baking soda, salt and orange peel.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg white; whip in oil, molasses and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in raisins. Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin pans or pans prepared with nonstick vegetable spray.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Stir in melted butter.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add chopped nuts and undrained pineapple. Stir just enough to combine.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add bananas and mix well until smooth.

title: chocolate sheet cake(serves 24)
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and resift with sugar and salt.
In saucepan, put butter, shortening, water and cocoa. Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, put eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Add to mixture and mix well. Bake in greased and floured shallow 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch cake pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Start icing the last 5 minutes the cake is baking.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts, dates and maraschino cherries.
Shape into balls.
Roll balls in cornflakes and top with 1/4 maraschino cherry.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Add hot water until desired thickness.
You want it
a little runny.
Heat until boiling.
Remove from heat and eat with biscuits.
Sounds different, but give it a try!

title: western baked beans
directions: Saute onions in butter. Combine all ingredients except beans and bacon. Mix in beans and crumbled bacon. Pour into 2-quart casserole and lay strips of bacon on top of bean mixture. Bake at 400°, covered, for 20 minutes, then uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into small balls and bake for 15 to 20 minutes on greased pan at 350°.

title: plum tart
directions: Crust:
Mix 2 cups flour, 1/4 cups sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Cut in butter until particles resemble coarse crumbs.
Beat egg with rum and lemon peel.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix quickly with fingers to form a smooth dough.
Press dough in bottom and 1-inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan (dough should be at least 3/8-inch thick around sides).
Flute edge, if desired.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well. Add chicken breasts and cover. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix
ground beef, cracker crumbs, onion, milk and salt. Roll into
balls and dip in flour and brown.
Separate pineapple juice and add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce,
brown sugar and lemon juice.
Cook until thick.
Add pineapple and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over meatballs and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt bark in microwave.
Mix pretzels and peanuts into melted bark.
Drop on wax paper by the tablespoon.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix milk and ground chuck.
Divide into four large patties. Mix stuffing according to package directions.
Place 1/4 of stuffing in middle of each patty and pinch patty together around stuffing.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Heat in saucepan and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: First you put milk and sprinkles in it, then raisins and salt, then you bake it in the oven for 20 minutes, then you put the chocolate in and bake it again and put it in there for 40 hours and that's it.
You have a nice chocolate cake.
If you want you can put frosting and sprinkles on top.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Melt butter; mix with flour.
Grate cheeses.
Add all ingredients in large saucepan; heat to melt.
Stir often.
Pour into fondue pot.
Serve with cubed bread.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Spread chicken parts over bottom of baking pan; do not pile. Mix soup mix, preserves and dressing together.
Spread over top of chicken.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(If it looks too dry, cover with loose foil.)

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool for approximately 20 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut oleo into flour and confectioners sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour filling over baked crust.
Bake another 25 minutes and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: scottish pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown beef in shortening in Dutch oven. Arrange vegetables around meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top meat with apricots and mushrooms.
Pour catsup over all. Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Baste occasionally.
Add a little water if needed.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: In medium bowl, add softened cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar in small amounts, beating after each addition.
Beat this mixture about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour in small amounts, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well but not too much.
Add one or all three flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rice pilaff
directions: Melt oleo; add washed rice and rest of ingredients except consomme.
Simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Add 2 cans of consomme and cook, covered, 1 hour at 350° in oven.
Look at, after 45 minutes, for dryness; if dry, add last can of consomme and finish cooking.

title: cheese balls(biscuits)
directions: Mix and shape into 1-inch balls, thumbprint.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
These are great at "Salad Suppers".

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and celery seed.
Boil sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over cabbage while hot. Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Best made the day before serving. It will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks or more.

title: apple souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium saucepan combine apples, apple juice concentrate, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until liquid is evaporated and apples are soft, about 9 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool slightly.
Transfer to a food processor fitted with steel blade and puree (small apple bits may still be visible).
Pour into mixing bowl.
Butter bottoms and sides of 8 individual 1 1/4 cup souffle cups.

title: hulushki
directions: Chop bacon in large chunks and brown.
Add shredded cabbage and cook, covered.
While that is cooking, shred potatoes.
Mix with eggs and add flour to make a noodle-like dough.
Spoon thick dough by heaping teaspoonfuls into boiling water.
Push down 3 or 4 times to get cooked through.
Drain noodle balls and rinse with hot water.
Mix balls, bacon and cabbage.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into Pyrex dish (slightly greased). Cover with foil.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove foil. Put pie crust on top.
Bake about 12 minutes longer.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add beans.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool and then add to rest of ingredients.

title: night before french toast
directions: Use extra butter to grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch flat casserole. Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange in one layer in bottom of pan.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans and form into 2 or 3 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: savory yogurt chicken
directions: In a pie plate, stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, garlic powder, seasoned salt, oregano, thyme and pepper. Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Coat chicken with yogurt; roll in crumbs mixture.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Drizzle margarine or butter atop.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for approximately 30 minutes or until tender.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water until dissolved.
Add cold water.
When partly congealed, add cherries and nuts.
When congealed, add topping.

title: red beans and rice with smoked sausage
directions: Wash beans and put in crock-pot.
Add 3 cups water and cook beans for 1 hour on high.
Add ham seasoning; cook on low for 1 hour.
Add smoked sausage and cook on low for 1 hour.
Add seasonings to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: polish tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes. Add onion, basil, dill, parsley, salt and pepper. Toss. Add oil and vinegar; toss again.

title: squash roll
directions: 1. Heat milk, margarine, sugar, and salt until melted. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, squash, and 2 c. flour. 2. Add more flour to handle.
Knead 5 minutes.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Put into round cake pans, 9 around outside and 3 in center. 3. Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Add all together.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: sicilian stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix together all ingredients through the celery in
a
large Dutch oven and bake 4 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours more or until vegetables are tender.
Saute mushrooms over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and peas to stew and bake 15 minutes more. Discard bay leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: After boiling potatoes, cool under cold running water.
Cube potatoes.
Place in lidded bowl. Add 3/4 cup vinegar to potatoes. Place lid on bowl.
Rotate bowl slowly to allow vinegar to go all over potatoes. Chill overnight.
Thoroughly mix onion, celery, pepper, salt and celery seed.
Add flavoring mixture to vinegar marinated potatoes, mixing thoroughly.
Serves 7.

title: chili
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onions and green peppers until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid and remaining ingredients, except kidney beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir in kidney beans and heat through.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Cook in 1/2 cup salad oil about 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Put onions and celery in skillet and stir-fry 3 minutes over high heat.
Add 1/2 cup broth and cook 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce with remaining broth and pour over vegetables and cook until thick.
Add chicken, sprouts and cashews. Heat through and serve.
Do not cook too long.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits and pat dry with paper towels.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and curry powder, then sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle evenly over butter and fruit.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before rebaking.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: azteca casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Heat. Place 1 cup corn chips in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half of meat mixture and half of processed cheese spread.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with additional corn chips.

title: coated pecans
directions: Beat egg white and cold water in large bowl until frothy and toss in pecans; stir until coated.
Toss in remaining ingredients and stir until coated.
Place in oven on a buttered pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Saute butter, celery and chopped onions.
Add cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, chopped mushrooms and liquid smoke.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until bubbles all over, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large pot, melt butter and cook onions until tender and limp, but not brown, about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, boiling water and carrot.
Cook until potatoes are just barely done, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken broth, half and half, milk, salt, white pepper and cayenne.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place raw chicken on bottom of pan.
Spread onion, ground pepper and mushrooms (optional) over chicken.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Add taco sauce and tomatoes.
Crumble half of the chips in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add ground beef mixture.
Top with remaining chips and cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked brie
directions: Wrap Brie cheese with fillo dough.
Baste with melted butter. Bake at 350° until brown and cheese is slightly runny.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Add salt, pepper and margarine. Mix flour and milk together, then add to potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Serve over crackers.

title: red cabbage
directions: Trim cabbage and chop or shred.
Wash well and drain.
Melt butter in large pot and add sugar.
Fry until golden brown. Quickly throw in cabbage (stand back because it may splatter a little).
Toss cabbage.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar, caraway seed, apple, salt and pepper to taste and just enough water to prevent burning.
Simmer slowly, adding a little more water if necessary. Adjust seasonings; cabbage should have a sweet-sour flavor; add more sugar and/or vinegar to suit.
Simmer for approximately 30 to 40 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
This dish improves greatly with each reheating.

title: date orange slice cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients in order listed. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Let cool completely in pan.
Remove.

title: pumpkin milkshake
directions: Put in blender.
Put cover on blender.
Set the speed on low for 30 seconds. This makes one large or 2 small milkshakes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Boil and simmer 10 minutes. Strain spices. Add 1 cup orange juice. Makes 1 gallon.

title: untraditional oatmeal cookies
directions: First mash the bananas with a fork or blend in a blender to a liquid.
Place in a large bowl and mix the sugar, vanilla, and egg substitute with the bananas.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, baking powder, and soda.
Alternately add the flour mixture and the milk to the banana mixture, and finally add the nuts.

title: zesty shrimp dip(makes about 2 cups)
directions: In bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Boil all but vanilla for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: roasted fresh veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut up veggies; sprinkle with herbs and salt and pepper.
Drizzle with olive oil and mix well.
Roast about 30 minutes, stirring half-way through.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add a small amount of water to the first 2 ingredients and simmer together until tender. Drain and add the soup. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add the pimiento. Grease casserole and line bottom with bread crumbs. Heat 10 to 15 minutes in oven to brown crumbs.

title: gnocchi tomato sauce
directions: Melt butter and oil in bottom of pan.
Add onions, garlic, salt, pepper, rosemary, oregano, parsley, sage and thyme.
Simmer slowly until onions cook clear. Add tomato paste.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add 36 ounces hot water; stir well.
Bring to boil. Lower heat, simmer 3 hours, covered and 1/2 hour more with cover tilted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Grease 2 regular bread pans.
Loaf pans can be used if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Ovens vary.
Cool.

title: cocoa bread
directions: Mix the cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add the milk, which has been scalded, and the shortening.
Let stand until lukewarm and then add the yeast, which has been softened in the warm water.
Add enough flour to make a dough which can be handled; knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in a moderate oven.
Half a cup of chopped nuts may be added to the dough, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: kool kake
directions: Add lemon jello powder to dry cake mix.
Follow direction on box of cake mix, substituting 4 eggs for the number of eggs called for.
Mix and bake.
When cool, frost with Cool Whip.

title: citrus vegetable salad
directions: In bowl, toss all ingredients.
Chill well before serving. Makes 3 cups or 4 diet servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add one cup pecans and mix well. Refrigerate until firm and shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans before serving.
Serve with assortment of crackers.

title: almond peach torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put egg yolks in measuring cup.
Add water to 1/2 cup mark plus 2 Tbsp.
Beat cake mixture and yolk mixture together for 2 minutes.
Place in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar until peaks form.
Spread egg whites on top of cake mixture.
Sprinkle almonds over egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cake will puff up and settle on cooling.
Cool completely.
Spread whipped topping over top and arrange the peach filling over the top. Chill until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain off fat. Add onions, peppers and celery. Saute until celery is done. Add mustard, sugar, vinegar and garlic. Then add tomato sauce and beans last. Bake in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes. Excellent for potluck or covered dish dinners.

title: strawberry pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to package direction (add one extra egg). Take cake from oven.
Punch holes all over (a soda straw works well).
Pour over cake: Strawberry Pina Colada Mix and frozen strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with Angel Flake Coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: buckeyes
directions: Form first 5 ingredients into small balls and chill until firm. Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls with toothpicks into mixture.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: sukuma wiki and meat
directions: Melt shortening in a pan.
Add onion and fry until light brown.
Add meat, which has been cut into 1-inch chunks.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Fry until the meat is brown.
Add sliced tomatoes and continue frying.
Cut the sukuma into small pieces and add to pan.
Cover pan with a lid.
Continue to stir often until the sukuma is done.
Add hot water and mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with ugali or bread.

title: tropical carrots
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain. Combine rest of ingredients in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add carrots and cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Saute chopped onion in butter.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 350° covered.
Uncover and brown for about 15 minutes.

title: yum-yum or poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins, shortening, brown sugar, water and spices for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to cooked mixture.
Mix, stir in flavoring and nuts. Bake in slow oven 325° for 45 minutes.
Set aside for at least 2 days.
Serve in thin slices as fruit cake or just cut in squares.

title: mother's rice salad
directions: Prepare rice mixes as directed on box; add chopped artichoke hearts and other ingredients.
May need a little of the artichoke marinade to moisten, if desired.
Mix well and serve cold or warm.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper add beef and drain.
Pour into 3 qt. casserole dish.
Add crushed tomatoes and rice.
Salt and pepper and mix well.
(Flatten top smooth and add more pepper on top.)
Cover and cook for one hour on 350.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar, and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and allow to cool.
In a separate bowl, combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar and add to (cooled) pretzel mixture.
Mix well.
Add Cool-whip and pineapple.
Mix well and serve.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Sprinkle with powdered Jell-O.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Congeal.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, margarine, Crisco and salt in a large bowl. With a pastry blender, cut in until it is coarse like crumbs. Beat the egg and vinegar in a 1-cup measuring cup and fill the cup with cool water.
Add to dry mixture a small amount at a time. Mix with fork and form a ball just the size for one crust at a time.
This can be frozen and used later.

title: next best thing to billy ray cyrus cake
directions: Bake cake according to the package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and poke holes in the cake with a wooden spoon.
Do not poke holes all the way through. Pour sweetened condensed milk over holes while cake is hot.
Do not let milk seep down the sides of the cake or pan.
Let cool and then pour the ice cream topping over the holes and top of cake. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath candy bars. Refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook sausage and bacon until sausage is cooked through and bacon is crisp, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain well.
In large bowl, beat eggs and milk together.
Stir in sausage and bacon mixture, mustard, bread and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate until the next morning.

title: turkey enchilada
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms 5 to 8 minutes.
Add turkey and brown.
Add chicken stock and reduce liquid by half, stirring frequently.
Add garlic, tomato, tomato sauce and hot sauce.
Cook on low heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 of cheese mixture; stir in and let cool.
Lightly brown tortillas.
Dollop mixture in and add salsa to taste.
Roll tortillas; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with remaining cheese mixture.
Put in oven at 400° until cheese melts and browns, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with salsa.

title: tomato gravy(old recipe)
directions: Heat bacon drippings.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until brown.
Add milk, stirring, then water.
Stir until gravy is ready to eat.
Add tomatoes and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Good over biscuits.
Could be a complete meal.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to the box directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
When cake is done, punch holes in cake with a fork while still hot.
Combine sugar, lemon juice and butter; mix well.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool.

title: potato pudding or "kugelis"
directions: Peel and grate fine
the potatoes and onion.
Cut bacon crosswise into narrow strips
and fry until crisp.	Pour bacon and fat over potatoes.	Add hot milk.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time. Add salt and
pepper;
mix
well.	Pour
into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for
15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°, bake 45 minutes longer.
Cut into
squares	and serve hot with sour cream.

title: cola congealed salad
directions: Drain cherries and heat juice.
Dissolve jello in hot cherry juice.
Let cool completely.
Add Coke.
When slightly congealed, add cherries and nuts.
Pour into chilled mold.
Let get firm.

title: raspberry mint vinegar
directions: Put the mint leaves in a very clean 1-quart glass jar and bruise them with a wooden spoon.
Add the raspberries; mash them with a spoon.
Add the vinegar; let the mixture steep, covered with the lid, in a cool, dark place for at least 4 days and up to 2 weeks, depending on the strength desired.
Strain the vinegar through a fine sieve into a glass pitcher, discarding the solids, and pour it into 2 very clean 1/2-pint glass jars.
Add the mint sprigs and seal the jars with the lids.
Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of pie crusts.
Mix cream cheese with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Put over bananas.
Top with blueberry pie filling and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter.
Pour into baking dish. Cover with crushed corn flakes and dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Empty salmon with liquid into a bowl; pick out and discard apparent bones.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with a fork until mixture is firm enough to form into a loaf.
Place in a small loaf pan or pie pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes. Serve from the baking dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: Beat eggs until it turns yellow. Add vanilla and sugar; beat until it turns white. Add flour. Pour into 12 x 8-inch sheet pan. Cook in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Turn into a towel floured with confectioners sugar. Pull off paper, then roll up until cool. Unroll and spread jelly or ice cream. Roll back up; sprinkle sugar on top.

title: nachos new mexico style
directions: Cook cheeses and tomato juice over low heat until runny.
Pour over tortilla chips or keep in warming pan and use as dip.
You may serve with chopped jalapeno peppers, if desired.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix above ingredients together with mixer.
Beat only until well mixed.
Pour half of mixture into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together:
6 tablespoons brown sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter and then put the other half of batter over this.
Bake at 350° 50-60 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Sort and wash peas.
Cook peas and onion for about 45 minutes. Add carrots and celery and cook until almost done.
Add potato and cook.
Add salt and pepper.
(Add water if needed.)
Cook rice separate or pasta separate.
Add to soup.
Break pasta into small pieces.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put marshmallows on top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zesty stir-fry chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce, sherry, marmalade, cornstarch, ginger and red pepper flakes.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cook pea pods with salt in 2 tablespoons oil.
Drain and keep warm.

title: laura's fruit cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and blend well, then add all other ingredients.
Mix all real good and pour into a greased angel food pan.
Put into a cold oven at 250°.
Bake 2 1/2 hours. Check with toothpick at 2 1/2 hours.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone.
Mix with Veg-All and soups.
Pour in deep dish pie shell.
To get pie shell for top loose, run warm water over tin plate; turn over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash butter
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot and cook 8 to 10 hours (do not cover).

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, milk, bread crumbs and 1/2 package onion soup mix.
Make patties and cook in skillet.
Remove and drain. Mix water, cornstarch and remaining onion soup mix.
Place cooked patties back in skillet and pour mixture over patties.
Cook until thick.
Makes 6 servings.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a double plastic bag.
Shake well.
Prepare in a 10 x 15 x 4-inch pan with Pam or wipe well with oil.
Run chicken under cold water; let excess water drip off.

title: butterscotch syrup
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup and butter in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to soft ball stage (234°).
Cool 5 minutes and blend in cream.
Serve hot or cold. Makes about 2 cups.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients all together.
Then mix the rest of the ingredients with beef mixture.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with 1 cup grated Mozzarella cheese and one 3 1/2 ounce package of pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. May freeze prior to baking.

title: buttermilk jumbles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Add 2 cups flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix. Add remaining flour.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in dish and use this to add to mixture.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; cream until smooth.
Add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy; stir in vanilla. Cake can be frozen for 3 or 4 weeks.

title: hamburger bean dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, onion and beans.
Cook over medium heat for about 35 minutes.
Good with corn bread.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Mix meat, soups, enchilada sauce and olives.
Tear up tortillas in bottom of large baking dish. Layer one layer of tortillas, then one layer of cheese. Repeat layers again.
Depending on size of baking dish, you should have 2 to 3 layers.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a preheated oven.

title: turkey ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion.
Spread on turkey ham slices. Roll into logs and place toothpick about every 5/8 or 3/4-inch. Cover.
Chill.
Slice apart and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all in a bowl; mix.
Grease bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small slices in baking dish. Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour over potatoes.
Add enough milk to come up level with potatoes.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes. Dot small bits of oleo over top of casserole.
Sprinkle a little more salt and pepper on chops.
Bake about 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Or at 275° for 3 or 4 hours.
Be sure pork chops are done!
Never eat rare pork of any kind.
Chops may be turned over while baking to make certain they're cooked all the way through.

title: chuck roast and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large mixing bowl, blend mushroom soup, onion soup packet, tomatoes, spices and water together. Place chuck roast in a covered baking dish. Pour ingredients over the roast. Cut onion into quarters and add to the pan along the sides of the roast. Place lid on pan. Place in oven. Cook for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or until tender.

title: pasta with italian sausage sauce
directions: Wash kale and tear leaves off stems.
Cut into bite size pieces (discard stems).
Crumble sausage from casings into a large nonstick skillet. Stir over medium-high heat about 3 minutes until browned. Remove with a slotted spoon onto plate.
Add kale to skillet and toss about 45 seconds until bright green. Stir flour into broth.
Add to kale and bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes into skillet.
Drain beans and add along with the crushed red pepper. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sausage and simmer 1 minute longer. Toss with hot pasta.
Serves 5.

title: blueberry rhubarb jam
directions: Fruit may be left whole, crushed, blended or put through food processor, depending on your choice of consistency for your jam. Put fruit into 6 to 8-quart saucepan; stir in lemon juice.
Measure sugar; set aside.
Open Certo pouches and pour into cup.
Pour sugar into fruit and stir well.
Bring mixture to full, rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat and at once stir in Certo well.
Skim off foam, using large metal spoon; fill hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe rims of jars with damp cloth and cover with hot lids and screw bands.
Water bath 5 minutes, counting from time water returns to boil.
Let cool and check seals.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls on a cookie sheet and roll them out flat and press together.
Bake as directed.
Allow to cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread on first layer.
Chop vegetables very fine or in food processor.
Layer on top.
Cover with cheese.
Pat down and cut.

title: fillet of fish(microwave)
directions: In 8-inch microproof baking dish, place almonds and butter. Cook uncovered on High (maximum power) 5 minutes or until almonds and butter are golden brown.
Remove almonds and set aside.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: After cooking chicken, reserve 2 1/2 cups of stock to be used later.
Mix together the chicken, celery, celery soup, milk, 2 tablespoons butter, onion, chicken soup and 1/2 cup chicken stock and put into greased 13 x 9-inch baker.
Next, combine the stuffing mix, 2 cups chicken stock and 1 cup melted butter together.
Spoon over chicken mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bring to room temperature and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.
Remove foil after the first 15 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: In 2 quart saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add garlic.
Cook 3 minutes more.
Add potatoes, broth and milk.
Stir over medium heat until smooth.
Simmer an additional 8 minutes.
Add cheese and Tabasco sauce.
Stir gently until cheese melts and soup is hot.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: carrot (but you'll think it's pumpkin) pie
directions: Cool carrots thoroughly before adding other ingredients.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, set aside.
Pour off all but 3 T. fat, add onion and brown, add potatoes and water; cook covered 15 min. or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in salt, soups and milk, heat but DO NOT BOIL.
Garnish with bacon and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: labella lasagna
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and cook 1/2 hour.
Mix cheese and eggs with salt and pepper.
Layer, starting with sauce, then noodles, then Mozzarella cheese, then cheese mixture; repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl, set aside.
Cut chicken at joints; place in a row in roasting pan.
Place the sauce over the wings and bake until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: sweet 'n' sour kielbasa
directions: Boil kielbasa until cooked.
Let cool slightly and cut into slices.
Place in baking dish and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: olive dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate at least an hour.

title: critter's chocolate mousse
directions: First melt the chocolate.
In a bowl mix the butter, egg yolks and instant coffee.
In another bowl, mix cherry brandy or Bailey's Irish Cream, egg whites, salt and powdered sugar.
Mix the second bowl into the first bowl, then fold into the melted chocolate.
In a cold metal bowl, beat the whipping cream until thick.
Mix the whipping cream into the chocolate.
Place mixture into a cake tin. Chill for a day before serving.
Yields 2 cakes.

title: 6-layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs. Mix well. Add milk and flour alternately. Mix. Pour into 6 greased and floured cake pans. Bake about 15 minutes at 300°.

title: tofu dip or sandwich spread(high protein health food)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Keeps well under refrigeration.
Delicious on crackers or as a sandwich filling.

title: pemmican
directions: Dry deer meat in low oven.
Sprinkle water over strips of dried meat and pound with wooden mallet until there are no lumps. Mix meat and juneberries in a bowl.
One half cup sugar may be added.
Now add lard to make the mixture stick together.
Store in a covered jar or dish.

title: creamed cucumber salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers; chop onions.
Put onions and cucumbers in large bowl.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture and mix well. Cool for 6 to 8 hours.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cut into small pieces. Spread over buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and celery salt. Spread over chicken.
Crush crackers into crumbs and mix into melted margarine. Spread over chicken mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add water and rest of ingredients.

title: roll out sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, vanilla, salt and sour cream with soda.
Add flour and baking powder.
Roll out (not too thin). Cut with a cookie cutter.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
You may frost, if desired.

title: thick and chewy pizza dough
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in water.
Combine 2 1/2 cups of flour and the
salt.	Stir
in
the
yeast mixture.
Knead the dough about 10	minutes,
working
in
1/2 to 3/4 cup
more flour so that the dough is still soft but not sticky.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion and pepper in butter for 3 minutes; add ground chuck and brown meat, breaking up meat with a spoon as it cooks.
Add salt, monosodium glutamate (if you desire), pepper and sugar; stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: apple butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and lattice top with 8 strips of pie dough.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold with real whipped cream.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins. When cool, peel and cut into good size pieces.
Add pepper, pimento, onion, bread (cubed) and cheese (cubed). Add salt, pepper and parsley to taste and mix together. Place mixture in baking dish or casserole dish.
Pour warm milk and melted butter over it.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs over top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana coffee cake
directions: Mix eggs, shortening, sugar, bananas and flavorings.
When thoroughly mixed, add soda and buttermilk.
Add flour and nuts. Beat well, then pour into greased and floured pan.

title: barbecue chicken in oven
directions: Blend all ingredients; heat until dissolved.
Cut chicken up; skin.
Salt and pepper.
Line pan with foil.
Dip each piece in mixture and place on foil.
Pour remainder over and seal.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: In a skillet, melt butter.
Bread pork chops with flour; place in skillet.
Add garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Brown on both sides.
Place browned pork chops in a Pam sprayed casserole or baking dish.
In a quart measuring cup or large bowl, combine cream of celery soup with milk; mix well.
Cover entire pork chops with mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients, seasoning layers as added.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Check during baking.
If too dry, may need to add water.

title: carrot pineapple bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together well.
Sift together the cinnamon, flour, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make a well in the center and pour in all liquid ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Grease and flour 2 or 3 loaf pans.
Pour mixture into pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Can be frozen.

title: yvonne casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
Mix other ingredients and bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Cover with cracked ice and sprinkle with pickling salt.
Let set for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Rinse well.
This step insures crisp pickles!

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonful into small amount of hot oil.
Brown on one side and turn to brown other side.

title: cran-bam
directions: Stir together and freeze.

title: strawberry vanilla pudding
directions: Place angel food cake cubes in a 9 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine instant pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and beat at low speed until well blended.
Pour over cake cubes.
Set aside until firm.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add frozen berries.
Stir until gelatin begins to thicken.
Pour over pudding.
Do not stir!!
Chill until set.

title: watermelon rind
directions: Select melons with thick rinds.
Peel off all green portion, using only the white part of the rind.
Dice.
Soak in mild salt water overnight (1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon water).
Drain and cook in clear water for about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.

title: lemony vegetable salad
directions: Blanch carrots and green beans 3 minutes in salted boiling water.
Cool vegetables in ice water, then drain.
Toss carrots, beans, celery, red pepper, corn and onion in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon peel and pepper.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter in large container.
Get to boiling and then turn on simmer.
Cook 8 minutes by the clock. Remove from stove.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted. Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add nuts.
Pour in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Makes 5 pounds.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Line a regular loaf pan with Reynold's Wrap and put the mixed ingredients into it.
Cover meat loaf with Piquant Sauce.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: susie's goulash
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients together.
Stir in flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 8 ounces Mueller's Klop noodles and drain.
Combine all together, saving almost half of the grated cheese for top.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Then remove cover and add remaining cheese; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add soup and blend well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Reserve 1/2 cup dry ingredients in which to roll raisins or dates for easier mixing with the batter.
Add vanilla; pour into well greased 10 x 6 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese icing, sour cream or whipped cream.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper, and dry mustard.
Cut steak into serving size pieces and dredge in flour mixture.
Heat oil in skillet and brown steak on both sides.
Place in slow cooker.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours or high for 3-5 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl. In separate bowl, mix mayo, sugar and vinegar. Stir dressing into broccoli mixture. Stir in bacon. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 40 minutes at 300°.
Top with the remainder of the applesauce.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cream together margarine and brown sugar; add flour and nuts.
Mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserving 1 cup of mixture for topping, press remainder into bottom of pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Blend sugar with cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Spread over baked layer and sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In a glass baking dish, layer vegetables, repeating layers once.
Add oil and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Rotate dish every 5 minutes.

title: cranberry meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients, then combine last 3 ingredients.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt and pepper.
Cook box of shells as package states.
Drain ground beef and add egg, bread crumbs and cheeses (use only 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese).
Place shells stuffed side down in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce on shells and other 1/2 package of Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Drizzle margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk, flour and other ingredients.
Roll out on lightly floured board 1/4-inch thick. Cook at 300° until lightly browned.

title: braised shrimp with vegetables
directions: Remove shells and back veins from shrimp.
Cut broccoli into pieces.
Drain mushrooms.
Cut whole bamboo shoots into thin slices.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Stir-fry shrimp in oil until tender, about 3 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp with fork.
Add mayonnaise and blend.
Then add and blend the salt, pepper, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, onion juice and chili sauce.

title: copper pennies
directions: Simmer carrots in a little water until barely tender.
Drain. Turn into a large bowl and mix in the onion and pepper strips. Combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix into the vegetables and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
May be served as a vegetable or relish.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In a saucepan, melt peanut butter and margarine.
In a large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Place on waxed paper lined baking sheet.
Makes about 100 candies.

title: beef steak and tortilla bake
directions: Slice steak into 2 x 1/8-inch pieces.
Brown in shortening in skillet.
Pour off pan drippings.
Season with salt and pepper. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add to steak.
Cook, tightly covered, over low heat for 1 hour.
Add mushrooms, tomato sauce, enchilada sauce, 1/2 cup onion and garlic, mixing well.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes longer.
Dip tortillas in hot sauce. Place 2 teaspoons of onion on one side and roll up.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir 3/4 cup cheese into remaining sauce.
Spoon around rolled tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, tightly covered, at 350° for 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: knishes
directions: Mash
potatoes.
Mix with eggs until smooth.
Add enough of the flour and salt to make a dough that can be rolled.
Roll dough out
and
cut
into
individual
rounds.
Bake on a well greased pan in a 375° oven until brown or deep fry.

title: puff pastry rolls
directions: On flat pastry, spread mustard.
Arrange Prosciutto over mustard.
Cover the pastry.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Roll it up like a jelly roll starting with long end.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Flatten with your hand.
Chill 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg and water together and then brush over the rolls.
Bake 10 minutes until puffy and golden.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup with water, bring to a boil and add 1 cup rice. Reduce heat and let simmer until all water is absorbed.
Brown sausage.
Mix sausage and all other ingredients with rice mixture. Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pull meat off bones and put in casserole dish.
Mix together flour, buttermilk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix the pudding with pineapple.
Add whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill thoroughly and serve.

title: broccoli and cheese corn bread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients and spoon over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Put in freezer in grocery bag to freeze harder.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine cornstarch in beet juice (drained from beets) until smooth.
Stir in sugar.
Bring to boil; stir often.
When sauce is thick, stir in cooked beets.
Keep warm for 1/2 hour to blend flavors.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg.
Mix well and serve warm.

title: squaw bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Place onto floured board.
Flour hands and pinch off dough, rolling into sticks about twice as thick as the size of a pencil.
Drop into deep bacon fat and fry until brown.
May also roll out and cut into strips or squares and fry in hot fat.
Delicious with beans.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine vegetables; mix well.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Pour over vegetables.
Cool.
Place in covered container.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in one long baking dish or two smaller ones.
Bake at 400° without cover for 25 to 30 minutes. May be frozen and cooked later.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Pour milk in slowly.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Cook on medium heat until cheese has melted. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: valentine butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Cut with cookie cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Decorate with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Yields 18 to 19 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Cook first four ingredients in large pot until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add next three ingredients and bring to simmer.
Combine sour cream and flour; add to soup.
Stir until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: no toss salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in square Tupperware dish. Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.
Cover with layer of mayonnaise (1 cup to 1 pint).
Cover tightly.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Before serving, add eggs, grated on top.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Do not toss.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put apples in a bowl.
Mix 1/4 cup of sugar with cinnamon.
Mix oil and remaining 2 1/4 cups of sugar until fluffy; cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients; add juice and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Place 1/2 batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Layer apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Cover apples with remaining butter.
Bake; cool on a rack.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Prepare crust and let cool.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and yolk.
Add vanilla.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Press dough evenly over a cookie sheet.
Beat egg white and slightly spread over dough.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over egg white.
Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: beef sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate. Remove once a day for 3 days and knead well for 5 minutes.
On the 4th day, divide mixture into 6 equal rolls or logs.
Lay on rack in broiler pan or drip pan.
Bake 9 hours at 160°.
Turn over in about 4 1/2 hours.
At 9th hour, wrap in paper towels to remove grease.
Wrap each roll in Handi-Wrap or freezer wrap. Refrigerate or freeze or eat now.
These keep well or great snacks.

title: spicy shrimp and linguine
directions: Peel and devein shrimp and set aside.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute shrimp, celery and onion in oil in a large skillet, about 3 minutes, or until shrimp are pink.
Add tomatoes and next four ingredients, stirring well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Toss with linguine.
Yields 3 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by teaspoonful in hot fat until browned.
Cool and roll in sugar while warm.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off fat.
Add beef (turkey); cook until brown.
Stir in garlic and onions; add undrained tomatoes, corn, salt and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Slowly stir in corn meal; cook until thickens.
Stir in olives.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole dish; add cheese and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Add jar of Prego, oregano, basil, parsley and garlic.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Mix in bowl cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.

title: country fried apples
