directions: Melt butter to generously cover bottom of skillet.
Place apples in skillet, making sure slices are thin.
No more than 1/4-inch thick; thinner is better.
Slow fry over medium heat with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Cook until transparent and soft. Serve hot.
Cook without peels is optional.

title: cinnamon (red) cucumber pickles
directions: Stage I:
Peel cucumbers, ream seed out and cut into rings. Soak in 1 cup of lime in one gallon of water for 24 hours.
Drain and soak in ice water for 3 hours.

title: muesli(swiss oatmeal)
directions: Mix all ingredients together the night before.
Chill and serve cold for breakfast.
A great alternative to hot oatmeal. Especially good on a warm summer morning.

title: sausage and cheese stuffed french toast
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, prepare sausages as label directs.
Drain.
While sausages are cooking, peel and slice kiwi fruit.
Rinse strawberries. Cut in half, if large.
Refrigerate. Cut eight 1 1/2-inch thick diagonal slices from bread, reserving ends for use another day.
Cut a pocket in each bread slice from top crust side almost, but not all the way through to bottom. Place Muenster cheese and sausage patties in pockets, cutting cheese and sausages to fit.
Press together.

title: tossed salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Peel cucumber (optional).
Slice very thin.
Chop tomato into bite-size morsels. Chop onion or slice very thin (amount varies to individual taste).
Slice radishes very thin.
Chop pepper.
Add black olives.
Toss with hands to mix thoroughly.
Season to taste.
Add wine vinegar and olive oil.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to marinate before serving with spaghetti and meatballs.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Melt over low heat the cocoa and oleo. Beat in sugar and eggs. Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Add nuts. Bake in greased pan at 350° for 20 to 24 minutes. About 5 minutes before done, top with marshmallows and place in oven to melt. Cool for a few minutes in pan and then spread the marshmallows. Put on icing.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook it until done.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Make up 1 recipe of Butter Buds.
Saute fish in Butter Buds and fresh minced garlic, about 1 minute.
Add scallops and shrimp and saute 1 1/2 minute more.
(Mixture will be thin; that's okay, the pasta will soak it up.)
Toss the fish with fettuccini, lemon, basil and salt and pepper.
Toss in Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan. Add cut up dates.
Boil slowly to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour at one end of a cloth dampened with cold water, squeeze water out and roll dough in cloth.
When cold, unroll and cut the loaf.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water 10 minutes or until tender; place 1/2 of it in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Cover with salmon and pour 1/2 of white sauce over fish.
Place carrots, peas and remaining macaroni on top.
Pour remaining white sauce over all.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coffee cream caramel
directions: Add milk to coffee.
Boil sugar, syrup and salt to firm ball stage (245°).
Add coffee mixture and butter very slowly, as boiling must not stop.
Cook and stir constantly to 242°.
Add vanilla.
Pour 3/4-inch deep in buttered pans.
Cool; mark in squares.
Chill until very firm.
Remove from pan and cut into squares.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: pastry puffs
directions: Bring water
to
boil
on
high
heat
in saucepan. Add butter; stir
until melted.
Turn heat down to low.
Add flour and salt;
stir
in vigorously.
Cook until mixture draws away from sides of
pan.
Remove
from heat and cool 1 minute;
add eggs, one at
a time and beat after each one until smooth.
On greased baking
sheet, drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stir-fry garden vegetables
directions: Fry potatoes until almost done.
Add all other ingredients. Fry until done.

title: foo-foo salad
directions: Drain cottage cheese and pineapple thoroughly.
Mix cheese, pineapple and dry gelatin together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 30 minutes before serving. In theory, this should serve 6 to 8, but watch out for a real "Foo-Foo" lover.
He can eat the whole thing!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs and spices together.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix together.
Place mixture in greased pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Mix in sugars and karo, cook 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat eggs and add to cooled mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Put pecans in pie crust and pour filling on top.
Bake at 300 degrees about 1 hour.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture; add alternately with milk beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla

title: sticky buns
directions: Using greased Bundt pan, plunk dough balls into pan night before. Sprinkle rolls with pudding and cinnamon. Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar and nuts. Pour this mixture over rolls and cover pan with foil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash in salt water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Mash and mix with other ingredients.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in a greased casserole dish in a 350° oven for at least 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place half the cake pieces in a flat layer in a rectangular pan (approximately 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch).
Reserve 1/3 cup of the cherry filling for garnish topping.
Spoon remainder of filling over the cake pieces.
Top with another flat layer of the remaining cake pieces.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream; beat with mixer on lowest speed until smooth.
Spoon evenly over cake pieces.
Chill at least 5 hours.
Cut into squares; garnish with cherry filling.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir together soups and milk.
Add turkey, cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Stir in uncooked noodles, coating with soup mixture.
Pour water over mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: frosted cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Remove woody base of cauliflower, but leave whole.
Aerate base with knife to make more porous.
Place in colander and cook, covered, six minutes per pound.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Season cauliflower, if desired.
In Tupperware cover, mix mayonnaise, salt and mustard.
Heat 45 seconds to 1 minute, uncovered, at 70% power.
Spread over cauliflower and sprinkle with grated cheese. Heat only one minute or until cheese melts at about 70% power. Sprinkle with paprika.
0ne-sixth equals 142 calories.
(Protein exchange and vegetable, 1 cup.)

title: jalapeno bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place sliced jalapenos on bottom of the pan.
Layer the Cheddar and Swiss cheeses.
Beat the eggs and pour over the cheese layers.
Top with sliced Muenster cheese.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Blot up oil with paper towel before serving.

title: betty's pound cake
directions: Mix oleo and Crisco. Add sugar and beat. Add eggs one at a time. Beat. Add flour and milk alternately. Add flavorings and beat well. Heat oven to 325° and cook 1 1/2 hours. Let cool in pan for 20 minutes. Turn out on cake plate.

title: reese cup cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Sift together with flour. Blend in shortening and 2/3 cup milk. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed or 300 strokes by hand. Blend in rest of milk, vanilla and eggs. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Grease and flour two 8-inch round or one 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: salmon teriyaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, wine, brown sugar and ginger in shallow non-metal dish.
Add salmon, turning several times to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, turning once.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs. Mix flour, spices and orange slices and pecans together and add to egg and sugar mixture. Drop by small teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°.

title: bejan's boranis(he named it spring salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Combine the ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly. Serve on lettuce and garnish with tomato wedges.
Serve with French dressing.
Serves 4.

title: troy's chops
directions: Use 1 tablespoon of oil in large skillet; salt and pepper chops.
Brown chops on both sides.
Slice onion and put 1 slice on each chop.
Slice pepper and scatter 4 to 5 slices around skillet. Quarter the potatoes and place around chops.
Quarter carrots and place in skillet.
Use 1 can soup to 3/4 can water.
Mix well and pour over everything.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wipe chicken pieces.
Dip into melted butter, then into crumbs.
Place on baking sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: big red cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as usual.
While cake is baking, mix jello and soda together in a bowl and set aside.
Prepare instant pudding and refrigerate.
When cake is done, cool for 20 to 30 minutes. Stab cake with fork (big holes), pour the soda and jello mixture over cake.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip together.
Pour and spread over cake.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Serve chilled.

title: baked mac & cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt butter in a pan, remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and bring to a boil while stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir macaroni, sauce mix, and 1 1/2 cup cheese in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.

title: pappy's tomato gravy
directions: Put bacon grease in pan.
Add flour.
Brown this.
Then add milk, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add nondairy creamer.
Continue stirring until thick.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Stir until hot. Remove from stove. Eat on bread, crackers, etc.

title: good southern hash
directions: Boil rice.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and bake in baking dish for about 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onion for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and paprika.
Stir in milk and stock and heat to boiling point, stirring frequently.
Soup will thicken and add vegetables. Serves 4.

title: chicken-spinach quiche
directions: Puncture a 9-inch pie shell and cook for 10 minutes at 350°. Add mixture and bake 1 hour or (1 hour and 15 minutes) and let sit 15 minutes before serving.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet and saut onion and garlic over medium heat, stirring until onion is transparent. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Simmer and uncover 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sauce should be thick but still juicy not dry. Cool. Refrigerate up to 2 weeks. Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly. Add milk and vanilla, stirring well, to make a smooth creamy mixture. Bring to a slow boil and then add butter.
Serve while hot with hot biscuits.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown the pork chops in oil. Place chops in an ungreased shallow baking pan. Toss bread cubes, butter, broth, celery, onion and poultry seasoning. Mound about 1/2 cup stuffing on each pork chop. Combine soup and water; pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until juices run clear and a meat thermometer reads 160° to 170°. Yield:
4 servings.

title: favorite family chili(serve with quick pita nachos)
directions: Prepare the pork; chop all the vegetables.
Spray a large Dutch oven with cooking spray; saute the pork cubes until no longer pink.
Add the chopped vegetables (not the mushrooms); saute about 3 minutes.
Add the canned tomatoes and the next 11 ingredients; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings to your taste.
Add some reserved bean liquid or more tomato paste to thicken slightly, if needed.
Add the kidney beans and mushrooms; cook about 10 minutes longer to heat through and blend flavors.
Serve over a bed of rice.
Serves 4.

title: john's gravy
directions: In hot skillet, blend bacon drippings and Bisquick.
In separate bowl, mix milk and water.
Add to skillet, stirring constantly.
Add Kitchen Bouquet.
Salt and pepper.
Continue stirring until thickened.

title: casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Heat to lukewarm:
cottage cheese, sugar and butter.
Combine softened yeast, cottage cheese, sugar, butter, salt, soda and egg.
Add flour to form a stiff dough. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Stir dough down; turn into well-greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, salt, pineapple, banana pieces and food coloring.
Lightly fold in nuts and cherries.
Spoon into fluted paper muffin cups (large size) which have been placed in 3-inch muffin cup pans.
Freeze.
Cover with plastic wrap and store in freezer.
(Fills 12 large muffin cups.)
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving to loosen paper cups from pan. Peel off paper cup and place salad on green lettuce leaf. Delicious!

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Stir in chicken, chilies, broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil. Add cream cheese.
Stir until melted. Spoon 1/3 cup mixture onto each tortilla. Roll up.
Place seam side down in an 8-inch pan.
Microwave Velveeta, milk and tomato on High 2 to 3 minutes until melted. Pour cheese over enchiladas.
To keep warm, place in a 350° oven or you can microwave them.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat until flavors blend (about 1 hour).
Add peeled shrimp.
Simmer another 20 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese fine.
Mix together all ingredients until mixed well.
Form into small balls.
Cook at 375° until golden brown.

title: orange slush
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and serve.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: In a quart pan, combine syrup and sugar; stir and bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over popcorn; toss until coated.
Butter hands; make balls and lay on wax paper.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press balls flat with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender or food processor and mix. Refrigerate at least 4 hours prior to serving.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Measure the sifted flour and sift again with soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and extracts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Put cake in a cold oven and set temperature at 300°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: philadelphia steak sandwich
directions: Cut up steak and saute in olive oil until pink.
Cut off top of bread and scoop out insides.
Place sauteed steak in loaf. Pour in enough pizza sauce to cover.
Place cheese on top of sauce.
Meanwhile, saute onion in steak pan.
Put loaf under broiler to melt cheese.
Add onion and peppers.
Put top back on loaf and cut in half or quarters to serve.

title: melissa's pizza
directions: Make crust according to package directions.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.
To baked crust, add sauce, then top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread together.
Place in hollowed-out bread just before ready to serve.

title: sour sweet pickles
directions: Wash
and
salt cucumbers, use enough salt and water to float an
egg.
Soak
overnight.
Next
morning,
drain.
Mix water, sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Drop cucumbers in hot
brine. When
they
change color, take them out and drain brine.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Let brine come to a boil and pour
over packed cucumbers.
Add dill, garlic and pepper pod and seal.

title: cantonese dinner
directions: Brown pork in skillet. Drain on paper towel. Combine all other ingredients with pork and return to skillet; cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until heated through. Serve over rice.

title: salsa
directions: Cook jalapenos in boiling water for 2 minutes; cook, then chop. Mix chopped jalapenos with all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Add to food processor for chopping to desired consistency.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan in a hot oven (400°).
Remove from oven as pieces of floured chicken are placed in pan.
Turn to coat with butter.
Then bake with skin side down in a single layer for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake another 30 minutes or until tender.

title: baked spaghetti(can be used with ground beef or ground turkey.)
directions: Brown ground beef (or turkey), onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Drain grease. Add Prego and simmer over medium heat. While simmering, boil spaghetti as directed on box and drain. Mix noodles and spaghetti sauce together and pour into a large baking dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Let stand for 2 to 5 minutes prior to serving.

title: quick breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage.
Line pizza pan with crescent rolls.
Crumble sausage over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over pizza. Add cheeses and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Add vinegar and food coloring.
Sift dry ingredients together about 3 times.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Layer ground beef, potatoes, beans and onion in a deep dish or crock-pot.
Pour the tomato soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or slow cook in a crock-pot.
Great with cornbread.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix the pork and beans, barbecue sauce, salt, pepper and onions together.
Add the hamburger.
Put into casserole dish.
Place 1/2 biscuits around edges and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick frozen jello dessert
directions: Will need 1 large size bowl.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan, greased and lightly floured.

title: lazy man cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (8 x 8-inch Corning Ware).
Mix together the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into dish and add fruit. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hummus(dip)
directions: Drain can of garbanzo beans.
Put all ingredients in blender or food processor and blend thoroughly!
Serve with pita bread wedges or crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients and put in 8 x 12-inch casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: hershey cookies
directions: Heat Hershey candy bar (over hot water) in double boiler.
Mix other ingredients in another bowl.
Pour chocolate over ingredients and mix well.
Make balls from mixture and cool.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies into crumbs and reserve 1/2 cup for the top. Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar mix well.
Fold in 1/2 of cool whip and spread over crumbs.
Chill 20 minutes.
Prepare chocolate pudding with 2 1/4 cups milk until its thick and spread over mixture and over the top.
Should be chilled 8 hours or overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli, scallions, garlic, basil and salt. Toss and stir-fry until broccoli is tender-crisp, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Toss with pasta, cheese and tomatoes in
a large bowl. Refrigerate.
Toss again before serving. Cheese tends to sink to bottom.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook until it boils and thickens, stirring continuously, about 10 minutes.
Allow to cool.
In a large bowl, combine whipped cream topping and cooled mixture. Stir in pineapple, apples, marshmallows and peanuts just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: Cut little pig sausage into little chunks.
In a medium-large soup pot over medium high heat, brown sausage.
As sausage is cooking and halfway done, add carrots and onions.
Continue to cook for 5-7 more minutes over medium heat settings.
Add cabbage. Continue to cook until vegetables become tender and sausage is no longer pink.
Add water if needed.
Cover and simmer.
Add seasonings and adjust flavor.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 4-h punch(serves 60)
directions: Combine drink mix, sugar, lemonade concentrate and pineapple juice in large container; mix well.
Chill until serving time. Add ginger ale, crushed ice and enough water to measure 3 gallons; mix gently.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except walnuts.
Form a ball.
Cover and chill.
Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: chicken veggie casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and almonds.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and almonds.
Allow cheese to melt before serving.

title: lettuce rolls
directions: Mix well and add:

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix both boxes of jello with the boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring thoroughly.
Chill until firm.

title: neopolitan squares
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs, butter, brown sugar and flour and spread in 7 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 275° oven.

title: date bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Half of mixture for top and bottom.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, butter, brown sugar and
3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool before pouring in dessert mix.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put chopped apples and sugar in mixing bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and mix good but not too long. Add nuts last, dredged in flour to keep them from coming to the top and mix well.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add salt and soda. Use 1 cup flour to flour nuts.
Roll in wax paper. Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Slice and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mom r's corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, milk and eggs thoroughly.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with crushed saltines, 2 pinches of salt, a sprinkle of pepper and dot with chunks of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pork loin
directions: Marinade pork loin in mixture of pineapple syrup, soy sauce, honey, garlic powder and ginger.
Roast in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours, basting every 10 minutes.
Cut roast in 10 pieces and insert pineapple slices between each portion.

title: best cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar. Press into bottom and up sides of spring-form pan.
Cream the cream cheese thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (no longer).
Remove from oven.
Heat oven to 450°.
Cream together sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Spread on top of cheesecake.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in a bowl.
Heat milk and butter together until quite warm.
Add to flour mixture and beat until combined.
Beat in eggs, then part of extra flour.
Put some of the flour on pastry cloth and add batter.
Knead, adding extra flour until smooth ball forms (maybe 5 to 10 minutes).
Cover with plastic wrap and let rest 20 minutes.
Form into desired shapes. Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 hour, until doubled. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Break cutlets into small pieces. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Coat with flour. Brown in hot oil.
Add water and simmer 2 to 4 minutes.
Add onion soup mix and mushrooms. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sour cream gently. Cover and cook about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over rice.
Can also be prepared with 1 1/2 lb. ground beef.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pack down for crust.
Take the Dream Whip and mix according to directions, then add 1/2 cup more powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Beat again until thick, then spread over graham cracker crumbs.
Add cherry pie filling and spread over top.
Chill and eat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, then mix with remaining ingredients as listed.
Bake in two 9-inch pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss cheese broils
directions: Mix all ingredients except toast.
Spread on Melba toast. Broil on top rack until cheese melts.

title: potato casserole bake
directions: Dump drained potatoes in baking dish.
Mix soups and cheeses in bowl and pour over potatoes.
Stir in ham, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: lime picklesdiagonal, iowa
directions: You may peel or leave the peeling on, but do slice or cut up and take out seeds of cucumbers.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil; do not brown (leave garlic whole; remove later if not desired).
Add tomatoes or tomato sauce and chosen herb.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for about 40 minutes.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: chili in bread bowls
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper. Add meat in batches. Toss to coat.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter in large shallow roasting pan (about 15 x 10 x 2 inches) in oven until melted.
Remove.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Makes about 9 cups. Party mix may be frozen, so save time and make a double batch. Thaw at room temperature.

title: rhubarb strawberry jello dessert
directions: Cook rhubarb in 1/2 cup of water.
Add sugar; simmer over low heat until tender.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides; season with salt and pepper.
Place in a large baking dish.
On top of each chop, place a slice of onion, pepper rings, rice and celery.
Pour tomatoes over chops. Bake, covered, at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Watch to see if additional tomato juice needs to be added.

title: peggy's punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a punch bowl. Stir until creamy.

title: ham
directions: Score ham, place cloves on ham.
Wrap in foil and bake 15 minutes per pound at 350°.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve with chips or in a salad.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Bake in 350° oven until set and begins to brown.
Cool.
Mix blueberry pie filling and lemon juice together.
Place over low heat and bring to boiling point.
Cool.
When both mixtures are cooled, pour blueberry mixture over cheese mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Test with pick.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan on both sides (no cooking oil). Mix onion soup mix and rice in a casserole dish.
Pour in water. Place pork chops on top and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: toasted almond balls
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits together over hot (not boiling) water; remove from heat.
With wooden spoon blend in powdered sugar, almond extract, sour cream, orange rind and salt. Stir in cake crumbs and chill until firm enough to handle, about 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in chopped toasted almonds.
Store in tightly covered container. Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl until dough does not stick to fingers.
You may need to add a little water.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Bring to a boil the water and sugar.
Add the fruit and cornstarch dissolved in a little water and boil all together, stirring constantly.
When boiling, remove from the fire and strain.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dutch country meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for a few minutes.
Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs, onion and seasoning.
Mix thoroughly and shape in a loaf.
Place in roasting pan; add 1/2 inch of water and bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In 1/4 cup margarine, cook onions until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add the meat.
Brown meat; add onions and mushrooms and 2/3 can of beef broth.
Simmer until steak is tender (about 1 hour).
Mix rest of broth with 2 1/2 tablespoons of flour.
Blend into meat and onions and thicken.
Just before you serve, add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: homemade frosty
directions: Place ingredients into blender or in a deep bowl and use hand mixer.
Blend or mix until smooth and creamy.
Makes 4 big frosties.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cheese together.
Add soup, shrimp and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: no-cook chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Press into pan.
Cut and serve.
Fast, easy and delicious.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together well.
Place in loaf pan and pour an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce over it.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine above ingredients with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased casserole dish (2-quart size) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; peel and whip.
Squeeze orange(s) into potatoes.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Add butter and whip.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Bake in souffle or casserole dish with marshmallows on top at 350° until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Make into rolls on waxed paper.
Chill well or overnight.
Slice thin and sprinkle with a little caraway seed.
Pat seed in a little gently.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until edges become slightly brown.

title: avocado dip
directions: Blend together until smooth, then cover and chill.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Transfer to a casserole dish.
Mix up a small amount of corn bread (thin) and pour over mixture.
Cook in oven at about 425° until corn bread browns.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place buttered bread in 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle browned sausage over bread and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.	Pour over mixture in baking dish and chill at least 8 to 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together beef, rice, salt, pepper and onion in large bowl. Shape into 2-inch balls. Mix tomato soup, water and ketchup in medium-sized heavy kettle or saucepan. Simmer over medium heat. Add meat balls. Adjust heat so mixture bubbles very gently. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until cooked through.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll into balls using about 1 teaspoon of dough.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° until the edges begin to brown (about 6 minutes).
Options to sweeten, before baking, make a thumbprint in each cookie and fill with chopped nuts or sugarless jam.

title: hot instant milk chocolate
directions: Mix together alternately in a large bowl or pan and store in airtight containers.
Use about 1/3 cup (or to taste) to 1 cup of boiling water.
May top with a marshmallow.

title: egg custard
directions: Put eggs in mixer and beat well.
Add all the other ingredients and continue beating.
Mixture will look real bubbly. I beat mine at least 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until custard is not liquid in center when you shake it.
Do not overcook or it will be watery.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Brown crushed noodles and almonds in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Save noodle seasoning for dressing. Dressing recipe separate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Optional: Green peppers, onion, black olives, green olives, sausage, mushrooms, crushed garlic or whatever you like on pizza.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion in safflower oil.
Add garlic.
Add carrots, celery, tomatoes, salt, white and cayenne peppers and 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 40 minutes.
Add green beans, macaroni, zucchini, spinach and navy beans.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes more.
Serve topped with a generous sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts soup.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix ingredients together in a heavy saucepan and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: frying cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Cool and drain.
Use water from raisins; bring to boil.
Cream fat and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonful and bake for 10 minutes at 410°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg and add other ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut into thin strips, let dry and put in boiling chicken or meat broth.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add other ingredients.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze and discard all moisture from spinach.
Combine all ingredients, except cabbage.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
To serve, hollow out a hole in the top of cabbage to house the dip.
May be necessary to cut off a portion of the bottom to make it sit upright.
Place dip inside; surround with crackers, chips or vegetables.
Serves 8.

title: pralines
directions: In heavy skillet, combine sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Add pecans.
Increase heat.
Cook to 234° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Let cook in pan 5 minutes.
Stir rapidly until mixture thickens and coats pecans lightly.
Drop rapidly from a spoon on foil or wax paper.
If too hard, add drops of hot water to desired consistency.

title: cranraspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in whole cranberry sauce and finally bananas and nuts.
Chill in 3 1/2 cup mold.
Can be served with sour cream.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Bake tortillas on ungreased griddle about 1 minute on each side. Keep warm in a damp towel.
Mix 1 can of chili, 2 tablespoons onions and 1 cup of the cheese.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of the chili mixture on center of each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Spoon remaining chili over tortillas. Sprinkle with remaining onions and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes until cheese is melted in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from stove. Add mayo and mustard; mix well.

title: elsie style chili
directions: Saute beef and onion until done.
Toast chili blend in skillet.
Do not scorch.
Add to meat; rinse remaining chili blend from skillet.
Pour over meat; add remaining ingredients and simmer in covered pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a 2-quart 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, place margarine in dish and place in oven.
Mix above ingredients, except apples.
When margarine has melted, pour mixture in dish and spoon in apples on top.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine; blend in cocoa.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add to margarine mixture.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake as directed at 350°.

title: simply delicious crawfish casserole
directions: In a double boiler, melt stick of margarine and add cubed cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons margarine and saute crawfish tails, onions, bell pepper and mushrooms until seasonings are limp.
Add the mushroom soup and cooked rice.
Stir in garlic salt and peppers.
Add the cream cheese and margarine mixture to crawfish mixture.
Stir and check for seasoning.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with grated Velveeta cheese and fried onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rice consomme casserole
directions: In 3 or 4-quart casserole, saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes with lid on.
Bake for 15 minutes more without the lid.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed and bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix the Kool-Aid as directed.
Use the boiling water to dissolve the Jell-O.
Mix lemonade according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt chocolate in 3 tablespoons of milk over low heat.
Blend sugar and creamed cheese until well mixed.
Add remainder of milk to chocolate and stir well.
Blend together the chocolate mixture and cheese mixture.
Gently fold in Cool Whip, mixing well.
Fold into the crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Set out for 1 hour prior to serving.

title: blackberry vinegar
directions: Crush berries in a large bowl; pour vinegar over top.
Stir with a plastic or wooden spoon to combine.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Strain mixture into a large saucepan; discard seeds.
Add sugar; bring to a simmer.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour vinegar into a decorative bottle.

title: six week muffins
directions: Basic Starter (One Version):

Dissolve 1 package active dry yeast in 3 cups warm water, using a glass or stainless steel bowl. Gradually stir in 3 1/2 cups all-purpose or unbleached flour. Cover with towel or cheesecloth; let stand in warm place (80° to 85°), free from draft, until starter begins to ferment, about 24 hours.
Bubbles will appear on surface of starter mixture.
If it has not begun to ferment within 24 hours, discard mixture and start again.

title: quick snacking crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 10 minutes at 250°, stirring once.
Very good as an appetizer with drinks.

title: chicken provincial dish
directions: Slice bell peppers in rings and cut into bite-size pieces; set aside.	Chop onion fine; set aside.
Cut chicken breasts in bite-size pieces.
Saut chicken in small amount of olive oil. Add red and green peppers and onion in skillet and saut.
Add tomatoes, garlic, wine and olives.	Simmer for 20 minutes.	Add spaghetti sauce and simmer another 20 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix.
Place into can. Add sweet milk and dairy milk.
Stir well.
Makes 4 quarts. Freeze in electric or hand crank freezer.

title: baked apples
directions: Core 6 large baking apples; pare strip off the top of each. Place in baking dish.
Fill apples with raisins.

title: pork and cumin
directions: Coat
pork
with
flour.
Heat	oil
in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Cook	and
stir pork over medium heat until brown. Drain. Cook
and
stir
onion and bacon in same skillet until bacon
is crisp.
Stir
in
pork
and
remaining ingredients, except	sour cream.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until pork
is tender, about 45 minutes.	Stir in sour cream, if desired, and heat until hot.
Makes 7 servings.

title: cherry pie jello
directions: Combine jello and water until jello dissolves.
Fold in pie filling.
Let chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and pour in loaf pan.

title: my mom's famous microwave fudge
directions: Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts and stir.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1 x 1-inch pieces. Yield: 1 1/4 pound.

title: peach surprise pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing well until well blended.
Spread onto bottom of crust.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until smooth and thick.
Cool completely.
Fold in 1 cup of Cool Whip. Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spicy banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients as listed. Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let chill 24 hours.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: In a saucepan bring sugar, syrup and water to a boil on high. Turn to low and cook to hard crackle stage.
Add cinnamon oil and food coloring.
Continue stirring while pouring into plastic ice trays.

title: just for kids: heather's dip its (snack)
directions: In a 3-section plate, heat wieners and melt cheese in microwave.
Remove plate and put Ranch dressing in the 3rd compartment of plate.
Dip wieners in either the cheese or dressing and eat.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Blend well and pour into 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch sheet pan. Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rum raisin ice cream
directions: Pour rum over raisins and set aside.
Bring 1/2 cup light cream to a boil; over low heat, add softened gelatin and sugar, mixing until dissolved.
Cool, then add remaining light cream, heavy cream, evaporated milk, rum extract and salt.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or longer.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze for 1/2 hour.
Add plumped raisins and rum and return to freezer for final freezing.

title: peanut butter cooked icing
directions: Beat margarine and Crisco.
Cook over medium heat until very thick, stirring constantly.
Will be very thick, like paste.
Put in refrigerator until cool.

title: torino dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Contains 3 calories per tablespoon.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks,flour, oleo and 1 cup of the sugar about 5 minutes.
Add
coconut,
vanilla
and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add
the	other
cup sugar.	Fold in with other mixture and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes or until pie is golden brown and firm.

title: debby's lasagna
directions: Brown meat with garlic.
Add sauces and simmer.
In a bowl, mix drained cottage cheese and drained spinach together.
Spray large pan.
Alternate sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, spinach mixture and grated Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover; bake 30 minutes or until done.
Uncover and let set 20 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; add package of quick thaw strawberries.
Stir until strawberries separate and gelatin begins to thicken.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: the black-eyed pea's baked squash
directions: Cut tips off squash and cut each squash into 3 or 4 pieces. Drop squash into a large saucepan with enough boiling water to cover.
Return to a boil, reduce heat and cook until tender.
Drain in colander; mash.
Combine with beaten eggs, bread crumbs, butter, sugar, salt, onion and pepper.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole that has been lightly greased or sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cover with a light layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes 10 servings.

title: three leaf salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Mix 7 pounds sliced cucumbers, water and lime.
Let soak for 24 hours.
Then wash 4 or 5 times, then soak in cold water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients; add to the cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Cook 45 minutes and put in jars and seal.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour; add cheese, seasonings and cereal. Shape dough into small balls and put on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with the back of your hand to form little wafers.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until softened.
Drain off all water.
Add all other ingredients except oleo and paprika.
Whip or mash until fluffy.
Add small amount of milk if needed.
Place in large casserole dish and refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Immediately before baking, drizzle melted oleo over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: agar agar srikaya(a cool, refreshing, typical java dessert)
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour into a 7 x 7-inch pan or dish.
Let cool in refrigerator until firm.
Cut and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare the potatoes and cut into thin slices.
Put a layer in a buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Repeat, having no more than 3 layers.
Add milk until it can be seen through the top layer.
Top with soup.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until the potatoes are tender.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreos.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half the cookies.
Mix pudding with milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cookies, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix with pudding.
Pour over cookies in pan.
Top with remaining crushed Oreos.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine; stir in the rest of the ingredients. Roll into small balls and lay on a cookie sheet.

title: chili chicken(low-fat)
directions: In water, mix onion and garlic.
Blend with spaghetti sauce, chili powder and Tabasco.
Layer rest of ingredients, alternating with sauce.
End with sauce, then Mozzarella.

title: uncle sam's delight(great july 4th dessert)
directions: Freeze half of the first 6 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add fresh strawberries and fresh blueberries.
Add other half and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 to 30 minutes before serving to thaw slightly.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and dice.
Put potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
In a double boiler, combine half and half cream, butter and 8 slices of Swiss cheese cut into small pieces. Add salt and pepper.
Cook this mixture until it thickens, keeping it smooth.
Pour this mixture over potatoes and allow to stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking and bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Allow to get golden brown on top.

title: four hour pork chop bake
directions: Brown as many pork chops as needed.
Remove from frying pan and place in a baking dish.
Make gravy with drippings and pour over pork chops.
Cover and allow to stand (can be made in morning).

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows. Refrigerate. Combine pineapple, juice, egg, sugar, flour and vinegar. Cook over medium heat until thickened. Refrigerate overnight. Combine pineapple-marshmallow mixture, sauce, peanuts, apples and Cool Whip; chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar. Beat until fluffy. Add corn syrup, butter, vanilla and pecans. Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: baked duck and oyster dressing
directions: Drain liquid from oysters. Add enough sweet milk to make 2 cups.
Crumble crackers into small pieces about 1/2-inch diameter. Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Stuff duck with dressing.
Put in greased roaster, breast side up.
Rub salt on outside of duck. Use remaining dressing around sides of duck. Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until tender when pricked with a fork.
Leave uncovered the last 10 minutes.

title: california slaw
directions: In a large salad bowl, place the cabbage, onion, green bell pepper, red bell pepper and carrot.
Combine the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and vegetable oil in the bowl with the vegetables. Toss the mixture until the vegetables are fully coated with the marinade.
Let marinate overnight.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Put half of crushed Butterfinger candy bars on bottom of 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish, then layer half of Cool Whip, layer of 6 ice cream sandwiches on top of Cool Whip and add remaining Cool Whip on sandwiches. Sprinkle rest of Butterfinger candy bars on top. Freeze.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from can of chunk pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Put liquid in a saucepan with tapioca. Cook until thickened.
Let cool and add pineapple chunks, banana chunks and mandarin orange segments.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix soup and tomatoes.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, make a layer of Doritos, chicken and soup mixture. Sprinkle cheese.
Continue with layers until all is used.
Top with cheese and bake in 350° oven until mixture is bubbly.

title: mound cake(single layer version.)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Meanwhile, combine milk and sugar in a saucepan.
Simmer until sugar dissolves.
Remove cake from oven when done.
With ice pick, make holes in cake.
Pour hot milk-sugar mixture over cake.
Before cake cools, spread on marshmallow cream.
After cake cools, cover with whipped topping. Sprinkle coconut over whipped topping.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, combine soups, rice, water and butter. Pour into greased 9 x 13 casserole dish. Place chicken on top of rice mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender. Enjoy.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add milk and pudding mix.
Mix.
Add Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Crush Oreos to fine crumbs.
Place half the crumbs on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in pudding mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine the meat, tomatoes (add more if necessary), carrots, onion, celery, bread and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover; bake in a 325° oven for about 3 1/2 hours, until meat and vegetables are tender.
Serve with French bread and green salad.

title: praline cookie
directions: Melt oleo, add sugar; allow to melt.
Cool.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Cook at 275° for 30 minutes.
Brown slightly under broiler, if desired.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: wild polk greens
directions: Cut
tender
polk
greens
in spring, when it begins to grow wild.
Clean
and wash thoroughly.	This cooks down like mustard greens, so you must figure on that when picking them. Put
greens in	large stock pot;
cover with water.
Let boil rapidly	over medium
heat.
Drain
very	well.
Repeat
the boiling and draining procedure twice more.

title: carolina cooler
directions: Combine pineapple juice and limeade in a punch bowl.
Pour chilled juices and ginger ale over ice cream.
Add ice cubes. Garnish with orange slices, strawberries or mint sprigs.

title: two week coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots in fine pieces.
Put remaining ingredients into saucepan and bring to boil.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables and let stand for 1 1/2 hours without stirring, then toss together and store in covered container.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: swiss steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Season and brown steak on both sides.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add wine.
Cover and cook 1 hour.
Add soup; cover and bake 1 hour longer.

title: eagle brand mayonnaise
directions: Mix eggs and Eagle Brand, beating rapidly.
Add vinegar slowly.
Finally, add salt and mustard.
Chill.
Stir before using.
Wonderful on potato salad.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Combine oil, sugar and vinegar in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook slowly 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine sauerkraut, celery and red pepper in bowl.
Add liquid and blend thoroughly.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight if possible.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix slightly thawed Cool Whip with sweetened condensed milk. Blend well.
Add strawberries with juice, crushed pineapple with juice and sliced bananas.
Stir until blended.
Top with chopped nuts.
Freeze overnight.
Take out 1 hour before serving to soften.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place bacon in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice over bacon.
Place chicken on rice.
Mix broth/water and soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle package of seasoning from rice box over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: date logs
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large sauce pan.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add rice cereal and chopepd pecans, mixing well.

title: cheezy chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly over bottom of glass ovenware. Pour chili over top; put cheese on top.
Heat oven at 350°.
Bake until cheese is melted and edges are boiling softly.
Can reheat over and over again.
Also, microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes.
Eat hot.
It's great.
Big hit at football games.

title: mom's turkey stuffing(for 12-pound turkey)
directions: In cuisinart, chop finely fennel, celery and scallions, Next finely chop chestnuts and walnuts.
Saute chopped sirloin in large pan until brown.
Add salt, pepper and 3 vegetable combination and half of the butter.
Stir well and add raisins, chestnuts and nuts.
Add rest of butter (more if needed) until mixture is well blended and somewhat moist.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together, then add eggs and beat well.
Mix in molasses.
Add the next 6 ingredients; mix well. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix well, except turkey, and let stand for a few minutes to absorb liquid.
Add turkey and mix well.
In a medium size casserole, form into a ring and spread sauce over top.
Cover and bake in microwave on High setting 11 to 15 minutes, depending on size of casserole, variations in microwaves, etc.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: hershey's brownies
directions: Beat butter on medium speed.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, then add syrup and flour.
Add the nuts.
Spread in a floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into bars.

title: peanut butter log
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into log. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 servings.

title: favorite chili con carne
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in hot oil in Dutch oven. Add ground beef; cook over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble beef.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Yield:
2 quarts.

title: lobster spread or dip
directions: Into the cream cheese, beat the Roquefort cheese, sour cream, garlic, onion, lemon juice and water.
Stir in lobster meat and its juice (if canned meat is used), breaking up the larger pieces. If you use fresh lobster, you may wish to thin the mixture slightly with cream.
Pile into a serving dish and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Could be put into an empty lobster shell.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Combine baking powder, soda, flour and salt.
Mix together the butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with sour cream to the creamed mixture. Add almond flavoring.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place layers in a deep clear bowl in the following order: white cake, strawberries with syrup, Cool Whip, coconut, pecans, cake, pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut, pecans.

title: texas style chili
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, onion, and garlic in a Dutch oven.
Cook until meat is brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain. Stir in next 6 ingredients and cover.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans and simmer an additional 20 minutes.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: daddy's special recipe bbq sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add vinegar, ketchup, hot sauce, peppers and juice of one lemon.
Drop 2 slices of remaining lemon in saucepan with above and boil.
Will keep for days.
It is the best sauce you'll ever taste and especially good on chicken!

title: salsa sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes in blender.
Pour into a bowl with rest of ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips, vegetable sticks, potato chips and toast.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hobo pies
directions: In tinfoil, dice the potato into chunks.
Put the meatballs, onion and spices all in the foil.
Put pat of butter on top.
Wrap the foil and place in campfire.
Cook on coals for about 20 minutes.
Great meal for camping.

title: salsa
directions: Grind tomatoes, chili and onion.
Add vinegar, oil, dash of salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot, cook spareribs and 1/2 teaspoon salt in boiling water to cover until tender, about 30 minutes.
In a small skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until golden, about 5 minutes.
Stir in ketchup, preserves, chili powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Heat to boiling.
Drain ribs and brush with sauce.
Cook ribs on outside grill or under inside broiler, brushing again with more sauce, until shiny and browned (5 to 7 minutes on each side). Makes 6 servings.

title: mija candy
directions: In a stainless steel or aluminum pan (do not use Teflon or nonstick) put first 4 ingredients.
Cook on high heat, stirring until mixture is the color of brown sugar.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Cover with chocolate chips, spreading evenly with spatula as they melt.
Sprinkle on almond slivers.
Cool.
This candy is like a Heath bar.

title: baked peach pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk and pour over bread crumbs. Cool; add sugar, beaten eggs, salt and nutmeg.
Mix and fold in sliced peaches.
Turn into buttered baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix flour and margarine and press into a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool crust.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Brown shells first, then set aside.
Cook the potatoes until done; pour off excess water.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into crusts.
Cook at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pennsylvania chicken noodle soup(microwave)
directions: In
a microsafe 3 quart casserole, combine the butter, celery, carrot and onion.
Microwave at High for 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Place the chicken breast on top of the vegetables and cover.
Microwave at High for 6 to 7 minutes until the chicken is done.

title: the best cookies in the world
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter.
Add egg and sugars and mix well.
Add flour alternately with salad oil, then add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Dip fork in 1/2 cup water and press down on each cookie.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Put on paper towels.
Drain.

title: spinach lasagne pinwheels
directions: Pour half of sauce into baking dish.
Combine spinach, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, egg and oregano; mix.
Top each noodle with 1/4 cup spinach mixture and 3 tablespoons Mozzarella cheese; roll up. Cut each roll in half crosswise.
Place rolls, cut side down, in sauce.
Top with remaining sauce; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Spoon sauce over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt dot's hungarian goulash
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir in sour cream before serving.
Cook noodles per directions.
Ladle mixture over noodles.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla, butter, and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shells through a tea strainer to catch lumps of cocoa.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Roll out, cut and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until faintly brown at 350°.
Frost them if you like with favorite frosting.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Pour all ingredients in bowl, except buttermilk; mix well.
Then add buttermilk and beat 15 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: blushing betty rhubarb
directions: Combine rhubarb and 3/4 c. sugar, toss so rhubarb is coated with sugar. Place in bottom of 8 inch round dish. Cream shortening, 1/3 c. sugar and vanilla, add egg. Beat until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk. Spoon batter over rhubarb. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Turn upside down to serve. Pass the cream.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Drain raspberries and pineapple, reserving juices.
Combine fruit juices and orange juice concentrate.
(Should be about 2 1/2 cups liquid.)
Combine boiling water and 1 cup fruit juice; bring to a boil.
Add to gelatin, stirring until dissolved; add remaining fruit juice.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold fruit into thickened gelatin.
Pour into 6 cup ring mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce, if desired.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, then mix in	other ingredients.
Pour into 2 regular pie shells or 1 deep dish
pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes or longer at 325° to 350°.
Bake until filling does not shake.

title: praline parfait pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stand whole chocolate wafers around the sides of a spring-form pan.
Roll the remaining chocolate wafers into fine crumbs.
Mix with butter and press into bottom of spring-form pan, making crust about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake for 7 minutes.
Cool.
Slightly soften ice cream and spoon half in spring-form pan.
Cover with caramel sauce, then sprinkle with pecans.
Top with remaining ice cream and freeze.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream and garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a baking dish, shred cabbage, making 1 layer, then spread hamburger over top to make 2nd layer.
Alternate hamburger and cabbage layers until the dish is full.
Pour 1 can of tomato soup over casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream.
Add herb crumbs and other ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
(Double for 12 but use only 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise.)

title: coffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 9 x 13 pan. In large bowl, cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, coffee and vanilla. Mix well. Sift flour and baking soda. Mix into butter mixture. Stir chocolate and pecans. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 20 minutes. Cool and cut into bars. Makes 16 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and beat with wire whisk. Chill.

title: pickled watermelon
directions: Tie spices in bag.
Boil them with vinegar and sugar for 15 minutes; add rind and cook until tender.
Fill hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: white pie
directions: Cook together the first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff and fold into first mixture before it cools.
Pour into baked pie shell.
After filling cools, spread a layer of Cool Whip on top of pie filling and sprinkle top with chopped nuts or halved maraschino cherries.

title: janice's pecan squares
directions: Mix and pour over hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool in pan before cutting into squares.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour and salt together 2 or 3 times.
Cream shortening or butter and the sugar.
Then beat egg and mix in with shortening and sugar.
When yeast is dissolved in water, add it to shortening mixture.
Add flour a little at a time.
Mix until flour is mixed in.
Cover with a wet towel or lid until you are ready to press it out.
Shape dough.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Arrange strawberries in heavy saucepan in alternate layers with sugar, making sugar the first layer.
Bring slowly to a boil and cook 9 minutes.
Add lemon juice and let stand overnight.
The next day, boil 9 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and tightly seal.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray. Heat over medium heat until hot. Add chicken and onion. Cook 5 minutes. Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in tomatoes, mixed vegetables and broth. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes or until slightly thickened. Add salt and pepper. Excellent with rice or cornbread.

title: garlic-mustard green beans
directions: Cook beans 20 minutes; drain.
Cook bacon and drain, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onion and garlic in drippings 3 minutes and stir in mustard, pepper and salt.
Cook 30 seconds more.
Toss with beans and sprinkle bacon on top.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix and sift cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add unbeaten egg yolks with milk and stir well.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie crust.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Can substitute 1 can mandarin oranges for 1 can of the pineapple chunks.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like a pie crust and put into a lightly oiled jelly roll pan. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Layer refried beans, avocado dip and sour cream mixture in a casserole dish.
Put tomatoes, olives, cheese and green onion on top.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix until batter is smooth.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. Bake about 20 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine pumpkin, apple butter, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Blend in eggs, evaporated milk and milk.
Turn into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Cool.
Top each serving with a spoonful of softened vanilla ice cream.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Combine and blend well.
Pour into a jar with an airtight closure.

title: broccoli penne pasta
directions: Cook pasta until just done. Drain and set aside.

title: aunt ruth's dumplings
directions: Cook chicken (have water covering it while cooking).
Add Crisco to 3/4 cup hot broth.
Mix with flour, a little at a time, and add egg.
It will take more flour to get dough dry.

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Lay crescent rolls out on cookie sheet where points are on the outside.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Fill center of crescent rolls.
Next bring in pointed edges of crescent rolls over mixture to look like braid, crossing one side then other side.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: cookie pops(easy for kids to make)
directions: You will also need 1 dozen popsicle sticks.

title: wild rice and vegetable salad
directions: Cook rice.
Whisk together with the first 6 ingredients.
Add vegetables and rice.

title: cheese and vegetable quiche
directions: Cook frozen vegetables until fully tender.
Shred all the fresh cheeses (unless already shredded).
Put vegetables in the pie shell.
Add onion, salt and pepper

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Lightly pack in 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes. Drain.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: davy crocketts
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Add the next 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Put into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on accuracy of your oven. Keep checking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl; add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Mix well.
Add the zucchini; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla until well blended.
Add zucchini. Beat until blended.
Add all dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes (loaves) or bake muffins 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil the butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put graham crackers in cookie sheet.
Pour butter mixture over crackers; spread nuts evenly. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Gradually beat in powdered sugar.
If too stiff to spread, add 1 or 2 tablespoons of milk. Use to frost cooled Carrot Cake (included in this cookbook).

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Delicious. Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cranberry sauce and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and pineapple.
Beat well and freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Whisk together applesauce, sugar, vanilla, egg whites and bananas. Add flour mixture all at once and mix gently. Pour into Teflon 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool completely before slicing.

title: chicken royale
directions: Take 1/2 of broth from chicken and cook 4 cups noodles.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top cooked noodles with layer of cooked chicken.
Break loaf bread as for dressing and add other half of broth.
Celery, onion and sage may be added. Put layer of dressing on top of chicken.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all while hot.
Cover with mini marshmallows.
Make icing and pour over this.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until set or overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: clam krisps
directions: Melt butter.
Brown onion in it; add garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, flour and minced clams with broth.
Cook until thickened.
Cut and remove crusts from bread.
Roll each slice with a rolling pin.
Spread clam mixture on bread.
Roll it up with fingers and cut in half.
Put on well-greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Cook for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix water and flour to a smooth texture. Add sugar. Bring to a boil. Add vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir until it is kind of gel-like.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add mustard and mayonnaise and pour over broccoli mixture.

title: shrimp etouffee(smother shrimp)
directions: Chop all vegetables very fine.
Heat margarine until bubbly, then add vegetables.
Fry until golden brown, then add drained tomatoes and half of the juice.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, seasoning and sherry.
Lower heat; cover and steam 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Season to taste the broccoli.
Mix and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with sharp cheese (grated) and crushed crackers with little butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In large saucepan of boiling water, simmer ribs about 5 minutes to remove excess fat.
Drain.
In shallow baking dish, combine remaining ingredients.
Add ribs and marinate 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Bring to boil first 6 ingredients.
Add spaghetti and cook until tender.
Then add Velveeta.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat until combined. Add remaining ingredients and beat well. Pour into floured cake pan 9 x 13 and bake 40-45 minutes at 350°.

title: janice's spaghetti pie
directions: Cook
spaghetti;
drain and add butter.
Cool slightly; add beaten
eggs
and grated cheese.
Form crust in a buttered 10-inch pie
plate	of
spaghetti.	Cover with cottage cheese. Brown beef; drain and add onion and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, sugar, salt
and
oregano;
heat through and pour into spaghetti crust. Bake,
uncovered,
at
for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello.
Add remaining ingredients in order, blending after each.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in egg and fruit cocktail. Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the nuts and brown sugar and sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake in 325° oven 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Place pieces of lettuce in bottom of flat baking dish. Sprinkle peas over lettuce.
Sprinkle celery and onion over mixture. Crumble crisp cooked bacon over mixture.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake as directed and put 1/2 of cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter and milk; stir over medium heat.
When melted and blended, pour over cake.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over cake and pour remaining cake over cake.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost with chocolate frosting and enjoy.

title: strawberry molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add remaining ingredients, including juices.
Pour into large Tupperware jello mold (6 cup). Chill overnight.
Turn out onto dish.
Remove top seal.
Jello should unmold itself.

title: mexican velveeta cheese roll
directions: With rolling pin, roll Velveeta between 2 layers of plastic wrap to 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove top layer of plastic wrap and spread cream cheese and chilies.
Holding onto bottom layer of plastic wrap, slowly roll cheese up jelly roll style.
Rewrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled.
Slice and spread on crackers.

title: festive punch
directions: Reconstitute the lemonade.
Add all ingredients. Stir.
Use an ice ring if you wish.

title: baking powder biscuits number 1
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Mix in egg and
milk.
Place
on
floured
board
and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1/2 cup shortening, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and egg.

title: rick's gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Place first 4 ingredients into bowl and beat lightly.
Add to bowl flour, salt, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to bowl boiling water and beat well.
Bake in a 9 x 14 x 2 1/2-inch pan at 350° until a testing stick comes out clean.
You can serve gingerbread directly from pan.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa; add margarine and milk in large sauce pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it begins to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, and vanilla.
Stir well and drop on waxed paper with spoon.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in greased 2-quart casserole. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until crumbs are brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pop the corn.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garlic powder, mixed.
Spritz with olive oil.

title: pepsi pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops and dredge in flour. Fry in oil on medium heat until browned on each side. Place chops in casserole dish with lid. Mix Pepsi and ketchup together and pour over chops. Cover and bake on 350° in oven for 45 minutes.

title: bavarian casserole(pork chops)
directions: Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan in layers just as given.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: finger paint(non eatable)
directions: Combine starch and cold water.
Add color to water; mix.
Add hot water; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and becomes clear.
Remove from heat and add soap flakes.

title: peach preserves
directions: Combine sugar and water in large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Add peaches; bring to boil and cook 20 minutes or until peaches are clear, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 12 to 18 hours in a cool place.

title: jewell's fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice and mix with Tang and pudding. Drain all other fruits completely.
Mix all together.

title: tortilla chips
directions: In a frying pan heat oil.
Place a whole tortilla (or cut tortilla into small triangles) into oil.
Cook only until bubbly and slightly brown.
Place into a bowl that has 2 paper towels in bottom.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage and cook in salted water.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain cabbage and put in pan.
Add to top of cabbage the butter, flour, salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Crush several crackers over top, then add dabs of butter.
Put in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: oven chop suey
directions: Cut up and brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a moderate oven for 1 1/2 hours.
When baked, top with 1 can chow mein noodles.
Serves 10.

title: orange balls
