directions: Mix wafers, sugar and orange juice together. Add butter and pecans, then form in bite size balls. Roll in coconut and refrigerate until firm.
Yields 36 balls.

title: punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Mash until soft.
Add Hawaiian Punch and pour ginger ale in slowly.
Stir gently until mixture is smooth.
Let set until foam settles.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together; bake in a tube pan or Bundt pan, well-greased and floured, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix cocoa and hot water.
Beat in a mixer or in a bowl with a hand mixer.
Bake in two layers at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
(Also good as coffee cake.)

title: apricot jello surprise
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Add cream cheese and stir to mix.
Add buttermilk, coconut and pecans.
Chill or cool before you stir in the Cool Whip.
Pour into pan and chill overnight.

title: barbecue cocktail wieners
directions: Brown wieners on medium heat.
Add barbecue sauce.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put toothpick in each wiener and serve.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Mixture will be coarse.
Form into ladyfinger shapes or roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 325° until lightly browned.
Remove to cooling racks.
Roll cooled cookies in powdered sugar.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: martha's vegetarian chili
directions: In a large pot, put in cumin, cayenne pepper and salt and heat for a couple of minutes (do not burn!).
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, beans and water and simmer.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off grease. Add green chiles and salt; simmer 10 minutes.
In a large casserole dish, place layer of corn tortillas, next layer beef mixture on tortillas, then put a layer of condensed cream of mushroom soup, then cheese.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: saucy italian roast
directions: Cut roast in half. Combine salt, garlic powder and pepper. Rub over both halves of the roast. Place in slow cooker. Top with mushrooms and onions. Combine spaghetti sauce and broth. Pour over roast. Cover. Cook on low 8 to 9 hours. Slice roast. Serve in sauce over pasta.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine 1 can of soup with 1 can of water in a large, square baking dish.
Stir in rice.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and
garlic salt.
In a small bowl, combine the other can of soup, sour cream and cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store mixture in an airtight container.

title: barbecued butterflied eye of round roast
directions: Combine beer, oil, vinegar, onion, garlic and pepper in a bowl.
Place roast in large glass dish.
Pour marinade over beef and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove roast from marinade and discard marinade. Grill beef on grill over medium hot charcoal to desired doneness. Turn and baste often with barbecue sauce.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces. Fry. Saute onion in bacon grease. Put sugar in with onion.
Mix onion, bacon, sugar and tomatoes together.
Put in a layer of kraut, noodles, some tomato mix, more kraut, noodles and tomato mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken parmesan(microwave)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Coat chicken on all sides and place in 11 x 7-inch microwave baking dish, meaty side up.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave 7 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn twice, until outer edge of chicken starts to turn opaque.
With meaty side still up, turn chicken so thick parts are facing outside of baking dish.
Cover and microwave 4 minutes longer.
Pour Italian soup over and around chicken.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Place 1 rounded teaspoon of mix in cup.
Add boiling water and enjoy.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar, flour, spices, soda and egg. Mix well and add pulp and nuts or raisins.	Bake at 300° for 20 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: mud pie
directions: Beat yolks with 1/4 cup sugar.
Dissolve instant coffee in 1/4 cup hot water; cool it.
When cool, add to egg yolk mixture and beat well.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in spring-form pan; freeze at least 6 hours.
Cover with chocolate syrup and freeze an hour longer or use strawberries and more whipped topping if you prefer.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix first five ingredients and let chill. Mix instant pudding according to directions on box. Mix well and put on top of chilled Jell-O mix. Serves 8.

title: souped-up chicken
directions: Melt butter; mix soups, rice and water.
Lay chicken on top or mix with soup mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, covered. Uncover and continue baking at 350° for 1 more hour.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Brown onions and green peppers in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients except butter beans.
Heat a few minutes. Put butter beans in a buttered 1-quart casserole dish; pour sauce over beans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix boiling water, jello, sugar and salt.
Let stand until soft set.
Add crushed pineapple and juice, pecans and celery. Then add cream cheese (at room temperature) and Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Fill a large pot with water and bring to a boil.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package. Drain and set aside. In a large skillet, brown chopped meat. Drain fat.
Add to sauce, paste and mushrooms. Set aside. Beat 2 eggs in medium mixing bowl.
Add the Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley and salt.
In lasagna pan, layer 1/2 noodles, spread with 1/2 Ricotta cheese mixture and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or assemble early and bake for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: my great aunt's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together lard, sugar and eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk; add molasses, then add spices and salt to the flour and sift in the dry ingredients.
Add just enough flour to make a soft dough. Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutter.
When cookies are on the baking sheet, moisten center of each with a cloth dipped in cold water and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat in 9-inch square pan.
I always double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
It doesn't last long.
It stays really moist.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
In large skillet, melt butter and brown meat and mushrooms; remove from skillet.
Into drippings in the skillet, stir flour and onion soup mix; gradually add water and reserved liquid.
Return meat and mushrooms to pan.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: scotch bread
directions: Mix all together and add 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into pan; the mixture will be stiff.
Ice with caramel icing if you like.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: special chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter or margarine, sugars, vanilla and the pudding mix.
Mix until creamy, beat in eggs.
Add flour and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon smoothly rounded and 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375 oven for 8-10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Beat eggs. Add fruit cocktail (juice and all). Add this to flour mixture and stir. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies (from top to bottom lengthwise); place, cream side down, in a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: no-bake chocolate peanut butter cookies*
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Stir quickly until combined.
Quickly drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla and mix well.
Mix in flour and baking soda.
Let dough stand 15 minutes.
Roll into walnut size balls, placing them 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
With plastic fork, flatten dough in a crisscross fashion 3 to 4 inches in diameter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Let cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: seven layer meal
directions: Into a 2-quart casserole, layer ingredients in order given. Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper as desired.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Hush puppies are good with this.

title: fresh tomato pie
directions: Bake and cool pie crust.
Peel, slice, salt tomatoes and drain 20 minutes on a cooling rack.
Mix basil, chives, onion. Grate cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Preheat oven 350.
Layer tomatoes, onion, basil, chives mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Spread cheese and mayonnaise on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: pam's chicken salad
directions: Boil whole fryer in water with oregano, 1/2 whole onion, 2 stalks celery and 1 or 2 garlic bulbs, mashed, until chicken is tender and fully cooked.
Remove chicken and debone.
Chop chicken up and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve after chilled.
This is a great dish for a luncheon.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Heat the tomatoes and juice. Add all the fresh vegetables.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Add everything else and cook slowly, about 30 minutes or until desired doneness.
(Shred cabbage into thin slivers.)

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Pour the macaroni in a bowl.
Wait for a very long time until it cooks.
It takes about 15 minutes.
When the timer goes off, you pour all the cheese on top.
When the timer goes off again it's ready.

title: tropical cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Press on bottom of 8-inch round or square cake pan.
Chill.
Whip cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple. Prepare topping acccording to package directions; fold into pineapple mixture.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: deep fried chicken
directions: Cook chicken pieces 20 minutes in water with 2 tablespoons salt and 2 onions, each cut into 4 wedges.
Wet chicken in 1/2 cup milk and 1 egg.
Let drip.
Roll in flour mixture; fry in oil about 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 1 can undiluted orange juice. Mix well and until thoroughly chill before serving.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Combine sugar, tea, cinnamon, cloves, water and juice.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil; stirring occasionally.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add buttermilk, whipping topping and nuts.
Stir and mix well. Pour in mold and chill until firm.
Slice in squares; serve on lettuce leaf with extra dot of topping and cherry on top.
Good recipe for diabetics!

title: cincinnati reds' tom humes peach cobbler
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder slowly with milk.
Add can of peaches; do not drain.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Best served a la mode.
Quick and yummy.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat together egg, sugar, milk.
Add vanilla.
Mix together and add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured cake pan and top with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in bowl (I put mine in a food processor) until they look like dirt.
In another bowl mix cream cheese and sugar.
Mix puddings and milk for 1 to 2 minutes with mixer.
Add pudding to creamed mixture.
Put in Cool Whip.
In a new 8-inch to 10-inch plastic flowerpot, layer cookies and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with cookies.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, insert stem of plastic or silk flower; add gummy worms in the dirt around the flowers.
I have hidden worms under two layers. They are surprised to dig out a worm.
I use a small flowering shovel to serve this.
I have also used a plastic sand pail and shovel.
The kids love it!

title: nutty cole slaw
directions: *These ingredients are mixed to individual taste and desired consistency.

title: green enchiladas(casserole)
directions: Mash and cook ground beef, drain oil.
One at a time, add chili and both cans of cream of mushroom, stirring to mix well after each item.
Heat five more minutes to blend ingredients.
Turn heat off. Cover bottom of pan with thin layer of mixture.
Tear each corn tortilla into 5 or 6 pieces (4 at a time).
Cover layer of mixture with pieces of corn tortilla.
Top with layer of mixture, generously, and sprinkle cheese on top.
Repeat 1 to 2 more layers of corn tortilla pieces, mixture and cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until corn tortillas soften, or microwave on High for at least 10 minutes.
Serve with rice and salad.
Yields approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water until tender; drain. Add parsley and butter.
Brown onion and hamburger.
Add oregano, salt, pepper, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in enough flour to thicken.
Stir in milk.
Layer noodles and hamburger mixture in casserole.
Bake at 400° at least 10 minutes or until ready to serve.
(Top with Mozzarella cheese.)

title: persimmon cookies
directions: You can also use dates.

title: tortellini and vegetables
directions: Cook tortellini in boiling salted water according to package directions, adding carrot during the last 5 minutes of cooking and the sugar snap peas during the last 1 minute of cooking; drain.

title: fruit breakfast
directions: Stir all together and top with additional granola, if desired.

title: mumph's cheese cake
directions: Cut cheese into large bowl.
Blend in ingredients, one at a time.
Do not overbeat, mixture should be a bit lumpy.
Pour mixture into spring-form pan.
Fill a large oven pan 1/4 way with water.
Put spring-form pan into water and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Turn oven off.
Leave oven door closed and leave in oven for 1 hour.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth on low.
Cook low but not dry. Saute bell pepper and onion.
Add other ingredients to spaghetti. Melt cheese in the vegetables after sauteed.
Mix with spaghetti and bake for 30 minutes.

title: baked potatoes, fried
directions: Bake potatoes in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done, but not overbaked.
Let potatoes cool and grate them as hash browns.
Fry in a small amount of oil or margarine until golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste and enjoy the best hash brown potatoes ever! Ketchup and onions are optional, yet very delicious!
Hot sauce is great, too.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually add peel and sugar.
Add egg yolks to butter mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter.
Pour batter into an 8-inch greased and floured round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: peach cobbler colonial
directions: Put peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Add milk and sugar mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over peaches.
Top with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch which have been mixed together.
Pour hot water over cobbler.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: roast beef in wine
directions: Prepare several days in advance and refrigerate.
Before serving, bake, covered, 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth and soup together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: beth's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck, drain.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for two hours on low heat.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: quick and elegant chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix together yogurt, onion, chicken broth and sherry.
Arrange chicken in a 2-quart shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cover with sliced mushrooms and yogurt mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, until done.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mom's slim guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 8.

title: grandma parker's apple salad
directions: Over medium heat, cook in saucepan the following: pineapple juice, flour, eggs and sugar.
Let mixture cool.
Fix Dream Whip according to directions and add to mixture.
Add nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Cut apples into chunks and add.
Mix well.

title: nacho pie
directions: Place chips in a lightly greased 9 inch pie plate and set aside. In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Season with salt and pepper. Spoon over chips. Top with beans, tomato sauce and mozzarella. Bake uncovered at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until heated through. 4 to 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and heat at 450°
for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cut slices of bread into cubes; set aside.
Mix shrimp (crab meat), mashed eggs and onion; add bread cubes and mix well, tossing with fork.
Add mayo and mix well.
Garnish with parsley flakes; cover.
Store in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce.
Serve with fresh tomatoes at side.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar over potatoes, also coconut (optional). Pour melted margarine over this.
Add chopped nuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberries in the snow
directions: Put cut up cake in bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in sugar and Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.
Layer cake and mixture until you have several layers.
Put pie filling on top.

title: strawberry pie(fat free and sugar free)
directions: Fill the crust with sliced strawberries.
In a saucepan, put the strawberry jell-o, the vanilla pudding, and the water.
Cook until red and clear; pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate for 2-3 hours.
Spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with berries.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: In bowl, mix cottage cheese and dry Jell-O real good.
Add pineapple and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 cup water and Crisco and heat until Crisco dissolves, let cool.
Add salt, sugar and beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add to mixture.
Work this into 6 cups flour.
Cover and let rise until doubles in bulk.
Punch down and refrigerate until needed.
Roll and place in greased muffin tin or cut into biscuits and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: chip dip
directions: Put cream cheese in the bottom of a low baking dish.
Put chili on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of chili.
Put in microwave until Cheddar cheese melts, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with chips.
Great.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in frying pan until lightly browned.
Add oats and mix well.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits.
Cool mixture thoroughly.
Beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, a teaspoon at a time.
Beat mixture until thick.
Fold in oat mixture, mixing well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Press pecan half into top of each cookie if you wish.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: super fluffy pancakes
directions: In
large bowl, mix milk, egg and oil with wire whisk.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat well.
Let sit in bowl for 5 minutes; pancakes will rise and get fluffy.
Pour into greased skillet; turn pancakes when bubbles appear, only turn once.
Makes 8 to 10 small pancakes.

title: chicken risotto
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; sprinkle with garlic salt. Melt margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet. Set aside.
Add water and contents of rice and seasoning packets to skillet.
Stir.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until most of water is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet.
Stir in pepper.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand until all water is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into ungreased baking dish.
Spread to corners of pan.
Add pineapple and spread evenly over the cherries.
Sift package of cake mix over this.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over the coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let set for a couple of hours before serving.

title: double chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Melt 1 cup semi-sweet morsels in heavy pan over low heat.
Set melted morsels aside.
Beat butter with mixer until fluffy. Gradually add 1 cup of sugar, beating well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add melted morsels and mix.
Combine flour and next three ingredients.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining morsels.
Roll dough into balls, one tablespoon at a time.
Roll balls in 1/2 cup of sugar.
Place on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pampered chef salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: Beat egg in large bowl. Stir in 1/3 cup of soup, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Add beef; mix gently. Shape into 6 oval patties. Brown in skillet over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes each side. Remove and set aside. Discard drippings.

title: company lasagna
directions: Cook beef until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Add garlic, parsley, basil, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Stir well.
Spread 1/2 cup meat mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer noodles, cheese mixture, Mozzarella and meat sauce.
Repeat as desired.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 3/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon in a large Ziploc bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Drop into bag and shake to coat biscuits.
Drop biscuits into a Bundt pan and layer with nuts.
Heat margarine and 1/2 cup sugar to boiling point.
Pour margarine and remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool several minutes and then flip onto plate and remove pan.

title: very hot dip
directions: Cook ingredients very slowly.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Heat pan at medium temperature with 2 tablespoons olive oil and 1 cup water.
Add vegetables, shrimp and sausage. Cook until tender and shrimp is pink, stirring often.
(May also use fresh tomatoes.)

title: men's favorite casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain fat.
Cook noodles; drain and add to meat mixture.
Add all remaining ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator to allow for flavors to blend. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 15 servings.

title: husband's delight casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, evaporated milk and onions. Brown meat in margarine; drain.
Add tomato sauce, salt, sugar, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook noodles; drain.

title: chicken or turkey bake
directions: Measure Croutettes into mixing bowl.
Lightly mix in butter or margarine.
Add hot water while tossing gently.
Spread in well-greased 1 1/2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Combine turkey or chicken with gravy or soup.
Spread over prepared stuffing. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
To serve, cut into squares and garnish with parsley sprigs or stuffed olive slices.
Serves 8.

title: feathery fudge cake
directions: Mix and cream well the sugar, margarine and eggs.
Blend in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt alternately with flour mixture and ice water.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon avocado spread
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Peel avocado, remove seeds and mash. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate before serving. Makes about 1 pint of spread.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine and 1 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat in creamed mixture.
Roll in balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in a mixture of 2 Tbsp. sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.
Heat oven to 400 degrees and bake for 8 - 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake. Serve with Town House crackers.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Bake pie crust at 425° for 10 minutes.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until it is reduced by half. Place cheese on baked crust.
Pour tomato mixture over the cheese.
Mix eggs and milk or cream and pour over the tomato mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce to 375° for 35 minutes or until set.
Let quiche rest for a few minutes before cutting.

title: freda's special brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine and let cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts; mix well.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and frost.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together well. Serve with chili dogs, chicken or your favorite meal.

title: al's strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, but put in (3)
8 inch pans, cool.
In bowl combine evaporated milk,
jello, (no water) and strawberries.
This mixture is called goop!
Make three layers in punch bowl.
Start with cake, prick holes in each piece. Then second layer is the goop.
Third layer Cool Whip.
Repeat for 3 layers.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, molasses and whiskey.
Sift dry ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup to dredge fruit in.
Add to egg mixture and fold in egg white.
Pour in greased and floured pan (tube or loaf).
Makes 2 large cakes.
Bake in slow oven at 275° about 3 to 4 hours or until done.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In stock pot, pour enough oil to cover bottom, then brown cubed steak.
Add remaining ingredients, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water.
Simmer for 2-3 hours.
May increase or decrease amounts depending on number to eat.
Great with corn muffins.

title: salmon patties 1
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Spoon into patties and fry in Crisco until brown.
Makes about 14 patties.

title: graham cracker eclair
directions: Beat pudding, milk and
powdered
sugar.
Fold
in Cool Whip. Line 9 x 13-inch pan
with graham crackers.
Put 1/2 of pudding mixture on top of
crackers.
Add
another
layer
of crackers and ice this layer with
icing.
Add
rest of pudding and another layer of iced crackers.

title: apple pie morning glory
directions: Make with or without pastry shell.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to the dry ingredients, stir until well combined.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; mix 2 minutes.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, allspice and cloves. Stir into Wesson oil mixture alternately with fruit juice.
Mix 1 cup flour, dates, mixed fruit, pineapple, raisins, cherries, figs and pecans.
Pour batter over fruit, mixing thoroughly.
Line 2 loaf pans with brown paper (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Pour batter in pans.
Place a pan of water on the lower oven rack.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours in 375° oven.
Let cakes stand 15 minutes before taking from pans.
Reynolds Wrap does better than brown paper.

title: shirt pocket sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, sour cream, vanilla and lemon extract until smooth and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients until blended, then add to the creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for one hour.
Roll out to about 3/8-inch thick and cut with a 3-inch biscuit cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake approximately 10 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: taboolch (salad)
directions: Soak Bargul in water for 30 minutes.
Chop onion, parsley, mint leaves and tomatoes very fine.
Add Bargul (after you have removed water from it), lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper.
Mix well and serve on fresh lettuce leaves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter. Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ali's quick cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften a little, then add salad dressing mix. Blend until both are completely mixed. Roll mixture into a ball. Place bread crumbs in a Ziploc bag (enough to cover ball). Roll ball in bread crumbs until completely covered. Wrap cheese ball in foil and place in refrigerator. Cheese ball will be ready the next day. Let it set out a bit before serving to soften. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Drain. Arrange layers or rice, sausage and onion in a greased casserole, ending with rice. Cover with soup. Season. Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Take crackers, margarine and 1 cup sugar and mix together. Use half for bottom and save other 1/2 for top.

title: rocky road
directions: In saucepan combine chips, milk and margarine.
Heat over low until chocolate melts; remove from heat.
In bowl mix together marshmallows and peanuts; fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in 9 X 13 pan, lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut and wrap in saran wrap.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, flour and nuts and flatten on cookie sheet.
Toast at 350° until brown.
Beat egg whites and sugar in large mixing bowl for 20 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream, whipped.
Add cut up strawberries.
Pour over baked crust.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Mix reserved juice together with all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Toss mixture just before serving. Makes 10 (1-cup) servings.

title: italian hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix Bisquick well; moisten with a little water.
Add remaining ingredients to Bisquick and mix well.
Shape into balls (size of walnuts).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel clusters
directions: Heat margarine or butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat until melted.
Stir in sugar, stirring continually, for 4 to 5 minutes while mixture melts and begins to turn golden.
Continue cooking 1 to 2 minutes until mixture is no longer granular and is lightly golden (mixture may be separated, that's okay).
Do not overcook! Remove from heat, quickly adding cereal.
Mix until cereal is coated completely.
Immediately spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool completely and break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 6 cups of candy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sift together first 6 ingredients.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, butter and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add and beat in zucchini.
Now add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into a greased pan and bake about 1 hour or until toothpick tests clean in center.

title: potato burgers
directions: Blend potato, beef, 1 tablespoon onion (3 teaspoons), salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon mustard and 1 tablespoon water.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot oil until crisp and brown. Remove from pan and keep warm.
Drain fat from pan; add to the pan the rest of the onion, mustard and water; heat and serve this over burgers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl, except pecans. Sprinkle with nuts when done.
Place in long cake pan (or several bowls for individual servings).
Freeze overnight.
Take out of freezer 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Keeps good in freezer if you want to keep it on hand.

title: lindbergh relish
directions: Grind the vegetables together; put in pan.
Add salt and cover with water; let stand 3 hours. Drain well. Add remaining ingredients. If vinegar doesn't cover, add more vinegar and sugar. Put in jars and can it.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and stir well.
Stir in corn syrup and mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir to a firm ball stage (245°).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool; cut in squares.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in 1-quart casserole; cover.
Microwave at High (100%) until apples are tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
Mash apples to desired consistency.
Serve warm or chilled.
Very good.

title: swiss cheese broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 10 x 6-inch dish.
In medium saucepan over high heat, steam broccoli.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt until smooth. Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and broccoli until cheese melts slightly.
Stir in eggs.
Pour in dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in serving dish and chill before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp well.
Heat soup.
Add gelatine, then cheese. Mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate. Serve with crackers.
Will mold very well.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of small casserole dish.
Spread cheese over top.
Cook juice, flour and sugar until boiling and smooth.
Pour over pineapple and cheese mixture.
Melt butter, add cracker crumbs and brown sugar and spread over top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In iron skillet, mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Make a nest in center and add egg yolks, stirring gradually, over low heat.
As it begins to thicken, add slowly 1 cup milk.
Cook until thick. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown top.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise into 4 to 6 pieces (unpeeled) into bowl of water.
Mix all dry ingredients well in shaker bag.
Coat potatoes, a few at a time, in mixture.
Dip in oil and place in baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Yum.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add chicken broth and potatoes. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and spices and cook for another 20 minutes.
If necessary thin with milk or cream.

title: soft butter cookies(candy canes)
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar.
Beat in egg, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, 1/2 at a time.
Roll out and cut cookies.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: beef tostada pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients (except the refried beans, cheese and Doritos chips) and simmer on low heat 30 minutes; stir often so it doesn't stick to bottom of pan.
In a 9 x 12 dish, layer the chips, then the refried beans and then the meat mixture.
Repeat the layers and then sprinkle cheese on top.
You may also add black olives to top if you like.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice according to package instructions.
In large ovenproof dish, beat eggs.
Whisk in vanilla, salt, sugar and milk.
Add cooked rice.
Place dish in larger ovenproof pan filled with 2 inches water.
Bake 30 minutes. Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture over rice.
Bake 30 more minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with whipped cream, optional.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla into a large bowl.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture; mix well.
Add cocoa to batter.
Spread batter into a pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Add shortening and molasses. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, salt and allspice. Add flour mixture and raisins to first mixture.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°.
Check after 15 minutes.
Should be lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Combine soup, beaten eggs, mayonnaise, chopped onion, broccoli, cheese, salt and pepper.
Bread crumbs may be used on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water; add cranberry juice cocktail; add 2 bottles ginger ale and stir.
When ready to serve, add softened vanilla ice cream.

title: sugar-free bread pudding
directions: Brush bread with melted margarine.
Mix 1 teaspoon sugar substitute and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over bread.
Quarter each bread slice.
Layer with raisins in 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Set dish aside.
Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and remaining sugar replacement.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Place dish in a pan containing hot water.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil and stir until dissolved.
To dissolved mixture, add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour mixture over corn flakes.
Fold until well mixed.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix and cover with Parmesan cheese and sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Bring to boil oleo and brown sugar; add vanilla and set aside. Cut biscuits into 3rds or 4ths each piece and shake in bag, few at a time.
Layer in greased baking pan or Bundt pan.
Pour brown sugar mix over each layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove immediately and pour over any excess topping.

title: baked chicken and broccoli
directions: Put cooked broccoli in bottom of dish, then spread chicken over broccoli and then cheese.
Mix curry powder, soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise together and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: red snapper amandine(microwave)
directions: Place fillets in 1 1/2-quart (10 x 6-inch) baking dish.
Rub lemon juice into fillets and salt lightly.
Cook, covered with wax paper or plastic wrap, 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Let stand, covered, while making sauce.
In a 1-cup measure or bowl, cook almonds and butter, uncovered, 4 minutes or until lightly brown, stirring twice.
Serve Amandine Sauce over fillets.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/3 of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer remaining ingredients, beginning with pudding, pie filling, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Repeat, ending with Cool Whip and sprinkle Cool Whip on top.
Best if made day before serving.

title: fruit burst cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in extract. Combine flour and salt. Add to butter mixture and blend well.
Shape tablespoon of dough into balls. Roll in nuts.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly.
Indent centers.
Fill with fruit spread. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire racks. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, creaming well.
Beat in egg yolks. Mix the dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Blend just to mix.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, chopped nuts and lemon peel.
Turn into 3 greased and lightly floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 or 60 minutes. Combine lemon juice and the 1/2 cup sugar.
Prick all over the tops of loaves with toothpick.
Spoon juice mixture over the hot loaves.
Cool 1 hour before removing from pans.
Cool for 24 hours before cutting to slice easily.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: breaded baked pork chops
directions: Mix
eggs and milk.
In another dish mix instant potato flakes,
salt
and
pepper.
Dip
pork
chops
in egg and milk mixture, then in potato flakes.
Place in baking dish and bake at 300° until brown.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend in blender for
5 minutes.
Then add 1 tablespoon celery seed.

title: potato bake
directions: Wash and cut Irish potatoes.
Coat with 1 package of onion soup mix.
(Shake together in bag or Tupperware.)
Place in baking dish.
Place in oven, covered.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.
Uncover last 10 minutes for proper browning.

title: dried fruit pies
directions: Cook fruit until tender. Start with fruit covered with water. Add more, if needed.
Mash and add sugar, butter and spices. Cool.

title: 15 minute super sundae pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir lightly softened ice cream until smooth.
Spoon the ice cream into the pie crust.
Cover with inverted plastic lid.
Place pie in freezer for several hours, until hard.

title: jiffy fudge
directions: Beat
cream
cheese until soft or smooth.
Slowly blend in sugar.
Add
melted chocolate; mix well.
Stir in vanilla, salt and
pecans.
Press
into well-greased pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.
Top each square with half walnut.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake for 15 or 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet (large) with foil, edges up.
Spray with Pam.
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers in cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove immediately and place on wire rack. Freezes well.

title: raspberry-rhubarb jam
directions: For thin jam, use 1 box jello; thick jam, use 2 boxes jello.

title: cornmeal pastry
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, sugar and salt.
With a fork, cut in butter and shortening until crumbly.
In separate bowl, mix vinegar, water and beaten egg.
Add to corn and flour mixture all at once.
Mix lightly, using fork until pastry holds together and sides of bowl are clean.
Wrap in plastic.
Chill thoroughly 3 to 4 hours.
Use as needed for pastry.
Can be stored in refrigerator for 2 weeks or frozen for 10 weeks.
Makes 5 single crust pies, depending on size or use for small tarts.
Scraps can be saved and rolled out again.
Make sure all utensils are cold.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and water; pour over chicken.
Mix self-rising flour, buttermilk and margarine; spread over soup.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer ingredients.
Use pie crust for bottom and top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Mix water, lemon juice and sugar in large pitcher until sugar is dissolved. Refrigerate hours or until chilled, if desired. Serve lemonade over ice. Garnish each serving with a lemon slice and cherry.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Drain and flake crabmeat.
Work softened cheese into crabmeat. Add sauce and onion.
Mix well and form a ball.
Mix catsup and horseradish together and pour over ball.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
the
ground
beef; drain.
Add sauce.
Cook noodles. Cover
bottom of pan with sauce.
Layer noodles, cheese and sauce. Keep
enough
of
sauce to cover top good.
Put in oven.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend and make into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bon bon cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Make walnut size balls and place on waxed paper.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and put on waxed paper. Store in refrigerator.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage leaves.
Wilt leaves for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Mix other ingredients together and place 1 tablespoon of this filling in each leaf.
Wrap and stick with a toothpick. Place rolls in buttered pan.
Baste with butter and bake 1 hour. Pour a little cream in juice and thicken with flour.
Pour over rolls to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Add flour and water. When thick, add Cheez Whiz.
Combine sauce with broccoli in greased casserole.
Top with buttered Ritz crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple butter stack cake
directions: Layer graham crackers and apple butter in a 9 x 12-inch dish until dish is full.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight and eat.

title: chocolate cream cheese dessert
directions: First Layer:
Cut 1 stick butter into 1 1/2 cups flour as pie crust.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, then bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat and dissolve jello.
Cool slightly.
Add cream cheese.
Beat cheese in cherries, cut in half.
Add to other ingredients.
Chill.

title: chocolate bar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Pat down on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: curry chicken
directions: Put cooked broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish. Put chicken on top.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin (dissolve completely).
Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: our best chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
May need to use more or less mayonnaise and light cream, depending on the moisture in the chicken.
Garnish with deviled eggs, stuffed celery, pineapple chunks, etc.

title: christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and milk in a pan and cook over low heat and stir until it boils.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin and cool.
When partially set, beat well.
Mix in vanilla.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Take 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff. Fold in cup of coconut and pecans.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix pudding, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Set aside. Grease Bundt pan.
Put frozen rolls in pan.
Pour margarine over rolls and sprinkle with dry mixture.
Cover.
Leave overnight or 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and then turn out on plate.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon in large kettle.
Remove, crumble and set aside. Drain corn and add to the liquid drippings in kettle.
Add potatoes, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and let simmer over low heat until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in the cream of mushroom soup, milk and crackers. Heat to boiling.
Just before serving, sprinkle crisp bacon over top of chowder.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add egg, orange rind and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hidden chicken
directions: Pour rice in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix water and both cans of soup.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture over the rice.
Add chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour the remaining soup mixture over the chicken; sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over the top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease cake pan.
Layer bottom of pan with 1 can crescent rolls.
Top with cheese slices.
On top of cheese, crumble uncooked sausage.
Top with eggs, mixed with milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Top with can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: victory garden vegetable soup
directions: Peel the potato and cut it into pieces.
Put the pieces in the small saucepan.
Cover them with cold water.
Slice the onion and celery.
Set them aside.
Peel and slice the carrots.
Peel and dice the turnips.
Slice fresh corn off the cob (or use frozen). Remove fresh peas from pod (or use frozen).
Cut tomatoes.
Cut lettuce into squares.

title: dirty cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and butter real well until creamy.
Fold into pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of square pan with cookies.
Pour half of mixture over cookies.
Repeat with rest of mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Crumble and brown sausage. Drain (reserve some fat) and set aside. In reserve fat, saut onions until cooked. Add celery and green pepper and saut until softened. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Place in a baking dish (one 9 x 13-inch or one 8 x 8-inch). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. (Can be frozen and thawed before baking.)

title: mexican rice and bean casserole
directions: Combine oil and water.
Heat to low boil.
Add onion, garlic, mushrooms and green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add rice, beans, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: nicholas' garlic steak
directions: Combine steak sauce, oil, pepper and garlic.
Place steak in plastic bag.
Add marinade, turning to coat.
Close bag securely and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour, turning once. Remove steak from marinade.
Place on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 4 inches from heat.
Broil 15 to 18 minutes to desired doneness (rare to medium rare), turning once. Serve with parslied potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scallops of venison with mustard sauce
directions: Season the venison to taste with salt and pepper.
Lightly dust with flour.
Place a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add clarified butter (or butter oil).
Cook venison pieces on each side just until edges are golden.
If using thicker steaks, cook on both sides until medium rare.
Juices should still be slightly pink. Transfer venison to a platter and keep warm.
Pour grease from pan. Add shallots, then vinegar, scrapping up any brown bits that may be stuck to the bottom.
Cook over medium heat until vinegar is reduced by half.
Add heavy cream and cook to thicken slightly. Remove from heat and stir in mustard.
Whisk in butter.
One piece at a time, spoon sauce over venison.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Place half noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread with half the cheese filling.
Add half Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares.
Filling will set slightly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Press into cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into serving pieces and brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt margarine and pour over apples to coat.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, and flour.
Mix with apples.
Put in pie shell and bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pigs in blanket(quick)
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In saucepan, mix soup and water; bring to a boil.
Spread cabbage, meat and rice in dish; mix.
Pour soup mixture over mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover tightly with foil.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Put drained carrots in covered dish.
Mix other ingredients well.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: almond poppy seed tea bread
directions: Blend together the flour, sugar, baking powder, eggs, milk, oil, vanilla, almond extract, and poppy seeds.
Pour into 2 large or 4 small greased bread tins.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Remove from pan and cool on wire racks.

title: applesauce currant spice squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch
baking pan with cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine currants with baking soda and boiling water.
Let stand 30 minutes in a medium size bowl.
Combine flour, cinnamon and salt.
In a large bowl, beat together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with currant mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix by hand until flour mixture is combined with currant mixture.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Remove loaf from pan. Place on wire rack to cool completely. Cut into squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oats.
Add oats.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender; cook ground beef and drain.
Mix with sauce; layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, noodles, sauce and then cheeses, until pan is full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen to be baked later.

title: chuck roast barbecue
directions: Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add beaten eggs. Add buttermilk, melted margarine and flavoring. Cook in double boiler until thick. Pour into cooked pie shell and cool.

title: apple chunk cake(thanksgiving is a great time for this.)
directions: Mix to make thin glaze.
Pour over cake.

title: doris' panama cake
directions: Mix sugar with egg yolks very well.
Add finely ground chocolate.
Beat egg whites stiff.
With mixer, add egg whites and finely ground almonds to batter.
Mix this slowly and well. Grease and flour an 8-inch layer cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
After cake is baked and cooled, cut it in half. Mix together butter, confectioners sugar and melted chocolate combined with 1 egg.
Put cream in middle and on top of layers. Serve small pieces.
It's very rich and very delicious!

title: baked pork with sweet potatoes and applesauce(diabetic)
directions: Spray 8 X8 inch baking dish.
Spray skillet with butter flavored spray and brown cutlets.
Place chops in baking dish. Arrange sweet potatoes over chops.
Combine applesauce, pie spice and brown sugar.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Cover and bake 50 to 60 minutes until sweet potatoes are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: cheese-pineapple salad
directions: Make lemon Jell-O according to directions on package.
Allow to set until it becomes syrupy.
Add the pineapple, pecans, whipped cream and grated Velveeta cheese.
This is a filling salad and can be used as a dessert.

title: melt in your mouth dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix lemon pudding according to box directions.
Spread on cheese layer.
Add remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.
(Preparation time 30 minutes.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, cornstarch and flour in saucepan on low until creamy.
Add egg yolks, salt, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in bowl and add vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line a buttered 9 x 13 casserole dish with half of the tortilla strips dipped in the chicken broth.
Layer chicken on top.
Mix the soups, Ro-Tel, 1/2 cup chicken broth and spices together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with the other half of tortilla strips and grated cheese (can freeze at this point).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: sweet and tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl. Use as barbecue sauce for poultry, beef or pork. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: green beans and broccoli
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Make sauce of soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir and pour over beans and broccoli in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered dry bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast shake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Makes 4 cups mix.
Nutritious and easy to carry on the trail.

title: chicken in a salad
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Tear chicken into small pieces.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to it.
Add chopped onion to this also.
Spread chicken in an oblong dish.
Mix 1 pint of sour cream and Miracle Whip together and spread on top of chicken.
Then layer chopped lettuce, then tomatoes, next bacon (crumbled), then grated cheese.
Top with crumbled Fritos.
Keep this in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar; cool.
Mix with above ingredients.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and press into a pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion and meat in shortening in fondue pot at high. Reduce heat to medium.
Mix cornstarch and seasonings into pizza sauce and add to mixture.
Stir well.
When mixture thickens and bubbles, add cheeses by thirds, stirring well after each addition. Serves 10 to 12 as appetizers.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut loaf of bread down the middle.
Mix mayonnaise, garlic salt and cheese all together.
Spread inside of bread.
Broil until light brown.

title: applesauce stack cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour or enough to make a good cookie dough.
Roll out and divide in five equal balls.
Pat out on a floured board to about 1/4-inch thick and place in greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: frito salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain well.
Drain and rinse Ranch Style beans.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook for 12 hours on low or 8 hours on high.

title: wild rice ring
directions: Rinse rice under cold running water until water is clear. Combine rice, water and salt in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour, or until rice is tender.
Add butter; stir well and pack into an 8-cup ovenproof mold.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Unmold and garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar with cocoa; add cornstarch and mix well. Separate eggs, save whites for meringue.
Beat yolks.
Set aside, add 1 can milk plus 1 can of water to the powder mixture.
Mix well over medium heat.
Add egg yolks before mixture is hot; let come to a full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baked deep dish 9-inch pie shell.

title: vegetable tray dip
directions: Combine dressing mix with sour cream.
Serve with raw vegetable tray of your choice:
sliced carrots and celery sticks, sliced sweet bell peppers, broccoli and cauliflower, flowerets, radishes, cherry tomatoes, etc.

title: salisbury steak with mushroom sauce
directions: Mix ground beef with next 3 ingredients.
Shape in patties. Brown in bacon drippings in skillet.
Remove to heated platter. Add flour to pan drippings, stirring constantly, until smooth. Add consomme.
Bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon over ground beef patties.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: california onion dip
directions: Mix milk and bouillon cubes in blender until bouillon dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients, except onion; blend at high speed until smooth.
Stir in onion.
Use as a dip for raw vegetables, toast strips or specially prepared tortilla shells, broken into pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, pudding mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mix lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cheese, sugar and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mix.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: peanut butter-hershey kisses
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter; add egg, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls. Roll in sugar and place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a Hershey Kiss on each; press down.
Return to oven for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: cream cheese jello
directions: Prepare your jello according to package directions.
Place it in the fridge until it begins to thicken.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo in a saucepan and melt together, stirring constantly.
Or, in a quart microwave-safe bowl, microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal into a gallon Ziploc bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely.
Shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool. Store in an airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: corned beef mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and set aside.
Mix other ingredients well.
Pour into Jell-O.
Pour into greased mold pan. Chill overnight.
Double for Tupperware mold.

title: jigglers
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water or juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours).

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in the top of a double boiler.
Cook, covered, over boiling water until rice is tender and milk is absorbed, about 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Soften yeast in warm potato water.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Loosely cover the bowl and set it aside in a warm place to ferment.
It takes 48 hours to ferment, after which the starter is placed in a jar with a lid and refrigerated to be used as needed.

title: easy popcorn topping
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan; boil while stirring. Pour over popped corn; stir and eat.
Store in open container.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, 3/4 cup of cheese, onion and lemon juice.
Spread in small, ovenproof dish (6 x 6-inch approximately).
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot with Waterman's crackers.

title: no bean chili
directions: In a large pot, cook Onion, Green Pepper, Beef and Chicken until meat is no longer pink.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Yields:
approximately 2 quarts.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Flour nuts and fruit, then mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
These will keep a long time and I store them in an airtight container with a piece of cut apple.

title: vanilla chip cookies(servings:  24)
directions: Cream together butter and honey.
Beat in egg, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Add flour gradually, then chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: ham ring-around
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients and set aside. On a greased cookie sheet, arrange triangles with points toward the outside in a circle with the bases overlapping.
Spoon filling over the bases and fold the points in under the bases of the triangles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: new potatoes and peas
directions: Scrub new potatoes or gently scrape off their papery skin. Cut in half and cook in a small amount of water until almost soft. Add peas and cook just until both are tender; salt.

title: snow balls
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Blend butter, sugar, and vanilla. Beat in egg.
Then blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Roll
into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: fruit pizert
directions: Spread on baked cookie.
Top with favorite fruit (ex. blueberries, strawberries, kiwi, pineapple, bananas, etc.).

title: sausage loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion; drain well.
Let frozen bread dough thaw.
Roll out to desired thickness, then spread half of the meat over rolled out dough.
Put 1 cup of cheese on top of meat (more if you like).
Roll this to make a loaf.
Repeat for other loaf.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until browned, about 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, brush with butter.

title: hoisin baby back ribs
directions: Cut racks into individual ribs.
Place in a large pot and cover with water.
Add slices of ginger.
Boil gently for about 1 hour.
Drain ribs and discard ginger.
Combine sugar, ketchup, soy sauce, oyster sauce, hoisin sauce, grated ginger, garlic and sake. Marinate the cooked ribs in this mixture for 45 hours in the refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put in blender green pepper and chopped onions.
Mix and put on wax paper.
Form into ball.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Shape more and roll in pecans.

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Spread cheese on each slice of bread.
Roll up like a jelly roll (the bread, not the cook!).
Dip in melted butter, then roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Cut into bite size pieces and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes great hors d'oeuvres.

title: california fruit salad
directions: Stir well all ingredients.
Add or delete fruits to suit your taste or to what is in season (i.e., grapes, plums, etc.).
Serve chilled.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Put chicken breasts, water, bay leaves and celery salt in large pot and simmer for 1 hour.
Cool and discard liquid, skin and bones.
Cook broccoli to package directions; drain and set aside.
In saucepan, mix milk, soft cream cheese, salt, garlic salt and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Stir; cook until thick.
Put broccoli in bottom of greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish and pour in 1 cup sauce.
Put in shredded chicken and pour in remaining sauce. Sprinkle with 2/3 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° covered.
Uncover, sprinkle cheese and chips on top.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Until cheese melts.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: ann's cinnamon rolls
directions: Recipe can be cut in half or one layer cake mix used.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and maple syrup.
Add egg and applesauce.
Sift salt, cloves, cinnamon, soda and flour.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well by hand only.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost with butter frosting.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut, gumdrops and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cocktail drop biscuits
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients by hand.
Drop walnut-sized onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° or until brown. These bite-sized biscuits are great for brunches and buffets.

title: lima bean chowder(real good)
directions: Fry bacon in large heavy skillet until brown.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until transparent.
Add broth, vegetables and herbs; cover over low heat for 25 minutes.
Put cream in small amount of hot mixture and add to rest of soup.
Simmer several more minutes, until soup is piping hot.
Serve soup hot with a bit of butter and a dash of paprika on each serving.
You could add some Cheddar.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg. Pat down into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and remaining eggs and pour over cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 45 minutes or longer until done.
Cool, refrigerate and cut.

title: sauteed steak and onion
directions: Wash steak and cut into strips; set aside.
Put butter in pan and melt.
Add steak, onion and bell pepper.
Brown.
When brown, add soy sauce and saute for 1 1/2 hours or 2 hours until tender on medium heat.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: rhoda's easy eggplant(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel eggplant and cut into lengthwise French-fry strips.
Prepare baking dish with nonstick spray.
Put eggplant in bottom of dish.
Peel garlic and cut into quarters and place on top of eggplant.
Spread tomato sauce over all and drizzle oil on top.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve over pasta.
If desired, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon grated cheese.

title: south-of-the-border stew
directions: *If a milder stew is desired, change to plain canned pinto beans.

title: croutons
directions: Cut bread into small cubes and saute in the oil and butter, stirring frequently, until golden brown on all sides.
Cool before serving with soups and salads.
Makes 3 cups.

title: forty-five day pickles
directions: Wash and cut off ends of cucumbers.
Pack in a big mouth jar with the cucumbers standing up.
Put 1 tablespoon pickling salt in the jar and fill the jar with vinegar.
Cover and allow to set for 45 days.
After the 45 days, rinse and chip the cucumbers.
Add to the cucumbers 5 pounds of sugar and 3 drops each of oil of cinnamon and oil of cloves.

title: super garden sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter and mayonnaise on bread.
Apply harvest and enjoy.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.
Cool (let it cool completely).
Then mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Spread on cool crust.
(Be sure to cover the whole thing or jello will go underneath.)
Mix jello and water well; add slightly thawed strawberries and stir well.
Pour it on top of the mixture "crust."
Refrigerate.

title: easy dump cake
directions: Pour the 2 cans of fruit in a long baking pan.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit and cut up oleo over top.
Bake 40 minutes or until brown at 350°.
When cool, cut in squares and top with topping or ice cream.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bake 4 minutes.
Bea together cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with cherries (2 cans).
You can then top with whipped cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat one minute.
Combine flour, soda, salt and apple pie spice; gradually add to sugar mixture, beating at low speed until blended.
Stir apples and pecans into the batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: keebler fifteen-minute lemon chiffon pie
directions: Pour chilled evaporated milk into a medium-size bowl and whip with an electric mixer until soft peaks form, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix water, lemon juice and gelatin in microwave bowl and heat on High for 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve gelatin.
Mix whipped milk, sugar, grated lemon peel and gelatin mixture with electric mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pout into pie crust.
Cover with inverted plastic dome and chill until fully set, at least 1 hour. Garnish with kiwi fruit, if desired.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Chilling time: 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello by package directions.
Put in refrigerator until almost set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with mayonnaise.

title: sally's spice tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 2 heaping teaspoons for each cup of boiling water.
Store in dry place in airtight container.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough into bottom of 12-inch round pizza pan. Bake at 325° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit of your choice over cream cheese mixture.
Mix orange juice, lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
When mixture is boiling, add 1/2 cup water in which 3 tablespoons cornstarch is dissolved.
Cook until mixture is thick and clear. Pour over fruit immediately.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream or topping of your choice.

title: vickie's cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cut cabbage in boiling water for 7 minutes.
In medium casserole dish, beginning and ending with cabbage, layer dish with cabbage and cheese.
Spread soup over ending cabbage.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over top.
Cook at 350° until crumbs turn brown.

title: classic turtle cheesecake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and press into 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt candy in milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Pour over crust. Top with pecans. In mixer, blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and blend in chocolate. Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool and chill.
Garnish with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown onion in butter; add tomatoes and chilies.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
(For extra zip, add some jalapeno relish or Tabasco sauce.)
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Serve with taco chips or bread sticks for dipping.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust - lay flat 2 tubes of crescent rolls on large cookie tin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Spread crust with cream cheese, mayonnaise, and ranch dressing mixture. Add grated carrots, cauliflower and broccoli pieces, and finely grated cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: apple pancakes
directions: In
medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in remaining ingredients; beat until well blended. Spoon batter
(about 3 tablespoons for each pancake) onto hot greased griddle.
When edges are lightly browned, turn to cook other side. Makes 10 pancakes.

title: lo-fat lemon whitefish bake(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 450°.
Baking Time: 10 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With sharp knife, cut beef into thin strips 1/4-inch thick. Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and oil.
Add beef.
Toss and coat meat with sauce.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
When ready to cook, put beef mixture into a hot, large frying pan or wok.
Heat until browned.
Taste meat.
If it is not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until tender over medium heat.
Add vegetables.
Toss until tender.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to pan; stir and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours until firm.

title: squash fritters
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar. Mix sour cream, egg and oil. Add to flour mixture. Add onion and squash. Spoon out into frying pan and fry until brown. Mixture may be refrigerated for several days.

title: saucy tomato rice cake
directions: Layer pan with sauce, then rice, sprinkle with cheese across pepperoni, spread sauce across top, then sprinkle with cheese.

title: becky's hot sweet mustard(this is great on ham or turkey sandwiches!)
directions: Mix into a paste the white vinegar and dry mustard.
Let set for 2 hours.
Add white sugar and eggs.
Beat all together.
Place this in a double boiler and cook until thick.
(Will probably have to let it boil for about 11 minutes.
It will leave marks when a wire whisk is stirred through.)

title: cranberry scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
In separate bowl, combine cream, egg and vanilla, whisking to blend.
Add wet ingredients to dry, stirring to combine well.
Dough will be sticky.
Stir cranberries into dough.
Roll dough out round on lightly floured surface to one-half-inch thickness and cut into pie-shaped wedges.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen wedges.

title: #2 easy ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fruit may also be added but sweeten fruit first.
Churn until frozen.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into loaf in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for one hour.
Let stand for five minutes before slicing.

title: broiled stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a small skillet.
Add chopped mushroom stems and onion. Saute 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove mixture to a bowl. Add remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix well and set aside. Dip mushroom caps in remaining butter. Spoon about 1 to 2 teaspoons of filling into each mushroom cap.
Preheat broiler in high position.
Place stuffed mushrooms on rack with stuffing up.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 24 appetizers or use as a garnish for main dishes.

title: mexican cornbread
