directions: Place beef and peppers in a skillet and cook until beef is brown.
In a bowl, mix together (with a spoon) cornmeal, salt, soda, milk, corn, eggs and bacon drippings.
Grease a large cast-iron skillet and heat until hot.
Pour in 1/2 of the cornmeal batter.
Cover with beef.
Sprinkle cheese over beef.
Pour on remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl; stir well.
Float orange and lemon slices on top.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and egg.
Combine molasses and hot water.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold into wet mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender at high speed until ice is chopped very, very fine.
Makes 3 large glasses.

title: best-ever banana bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt and set aside. Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in dry ingredients and bananas.
Do not beat.
Spoon into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: fruit studded yogurt
directions: Drain apricots; reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
In food processor or blender, combine apricots, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and reserved syrup.
Process until smooth puree.
Add yogurt; process until well combined.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan. Freeze 2 to 3 hours until firm.

title: phillip's poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all the ingredients into a small bowl.
Beat the mix until well blended and thickened.
Put in covered container and chill. Shake well before serving.
Makes approximately 1 3/4 cups.

title: cheese stuffed tomatoes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cheeses and seasonings.
Mix well. Spoon cheese mixture into tomatoes.
Cover and chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 30.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, butter and vanilla in a pan.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Take off stove and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal; mix.
Drop onto wax paper and cool or refrigerate.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Simmer pecans in margarine.
Mix Karo with eggs, flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.
Yield:
Two 9-inch pies.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix sugar and water; heat.
Add bananas, pineapple-grapefruit drink and orange juice; freeze.
Set out to thaw (but not completely) before serving.
Add ginger ale.
Rum may also be added.

title: vegetarian sierra stew
directions: Wash beans.
Place in large bowl and cover with water.
Soak overnight.
Rinse and set aside.
In dutch oven over medium heat, heat oil and saute onion and garlic 3 to 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper, cabbage, potatoes and tomatoes with liquid, chili powder and cumin.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently for 3 minutes. Add rice, water or broth and beans.
Cover and cook over low heat 2 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with pepper flavored Monterey Jack cheese, salsa or sour cream.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Arrange in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli. Mix together soup, curry powder, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour over chicken, then sprinkle with cheese.
Place bread crumbs on top and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Simmer chopped onion and bell pepper with margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place brisket on sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Add all the other ingredients, except the flour.
Bake 3 hours or until tender.
Slice the meat.
Skim off the fat from the gravy and thicken with flour.
Add mushrooms.
Return sliced meat to gravy and heat until bubbly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix
the
first five ingredients together on stove top. Bring to	a
hard
boil
for
one
minute;
remove from heat. Flatten cookie
dough on pizza pan.
Bake according to directions (or until cookie dough is lightly brown).

title: london broil
directions: Cut all fat and score flank steak.
Marinate overnight in gallon size Ziploc bag.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix everything together, except jello and Cool Whip.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Make jello and add 5 tablespoons to the mixture.
Let cool.
Then fill baked pie shell with sliced strawberries.
Pour filling over them.
Chill and cover with Cool Whip.

title: crabbies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Spread on halved, then quartered English muffins.
Broil 8 minutes or bake at 350° until brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and place in a casserole dish. While meat is browning, boil peeled sliced potatoes with butter and salt.
Drain and mash.
To mash potatoes, add sour cream, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Spoon potatoes over beef and cover with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until cheese begins to bubble.
Remove, cool and serve.

title: peach ambrosia
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir in peach halves and sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in whole egg and egg yolk.
Sift flour and soda with nutmeg.
Mix into batter.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto lightly buttered cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: easy mexican burritos
directions: Fry beef, onion, burrito seasoning and pepper together in large pan.
Drain fat; set aside.
Melt cheese in double boiler. When cheese has melted, stir in Ro-Tel tomatoes; stir until mixed well.
Put beef mixture in center of tortilla and roll up.
Place tortilla in a shallow pan.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Brown in oven for approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter granola breakfast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread oats on a baking sheet.
Bake 7 minutes or until golden, stirring occasionally.
In saucepan over low heat, stir peanut butter, honey and brown sugar until melted. In a large bowl, toss together oats and peanut butter mixture. Stir in wheat germ and cinnamon.

title: jello pudding in a cloud
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.

title: fumi salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, pepper, salt, Accent and oil for dressing into a container to refrigerate until ready to use.
Put sesame seed in a pie pan under the broiler for a few minutes stirring occasionally not to burn.
Put in jar or Baggie until ready to use.
When ready to serve, add all ingredients and toss. Keeps well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together shortening and butter.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 370° for 8 to 10 minutes.
For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done, then drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted (simmering for 10 minutes).

title: no meat lasagna
directions: Prepare 1/2 package lasagna according to package directions. Saute onions, celery and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and spices. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Crush noodles with your hands.
Place noodles in large serving bowl.
Add broccoli slaw, then sprinkle almonds, sunflower kernels and green onions.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from the 2 cans (or 1 pound) of minced clams and save juice.
Pour juice over 1 cup chopped onion, diced celery and potatoes.
Add enough water to cover.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat until barely tender.
Melt 3/4 cup butter in pan.
Add 3/4 cup flour.
Cook, simmering.
Stir constantly.
Add half and half and cook and stir until smooth and thick.
Add undrained vegetables, clams and red wine vinegar.
Heat through.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage and bean soup
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, cook sausage (medium heat) until it browns.
Drain.
Add olive oil, onion and garlic to sausage.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients to sausage mixture.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve at once.
Yields about 6 quarts.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Soak the chicken in the soy sauce. Roll in cornstarch. Fry chicken in oil until done. Take chicken up. Saute onions, carrots and bell pepper for about 5 minutes. Add chicken back to the vegetables.
Add sweet and sour sauce, pineapple and water chestnuts.
Let simmer until warm.
Serve over rice. Tastes great!

title: boiled custard
directions: Let milk come to boiling point. Mix sugar, salt and flour together. Beat egg and add to mixture until it is smooth. Add hot milk to mixture in a bowl a little at a time until it is smooth and then put back in boiler and cook. Cook, stirring until thick. Add vanilla when cool.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook and cool rice.
Put oil in frypan.
Add onion and mushrooms and brown.
Add soy sauce and rice; mix well.
Break eggs on top and mix well.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients with a folding motion.

title: mud cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (use rolling pin).
Mix with melted butter and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add ice cream or yogurt, softened.
Then spread hot fudge sauce over this. Last, spread Cool Whip and freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat margarine and sugar with mixer for 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Stir in bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add flour mixture gradually to batter.
Stir until well mixed. Add sour milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter into loaf pan. Sprinkle top with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until the center is baked when tested.
Cool 10 minutes in pan on wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars; beat in oil until well blended. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir in cream mixture.
Chill dough.
Shape into balls size of walnut.
Press down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° until set or light brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Measure.
Add baking soda and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg, alternating with dry ingredients.
Chill.
Remove.
Make balls 1-inch diameter.
Place on slightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with table fork dipped in flour.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: brownie drop cookies
directions: Melt squares and chocolate chips and butter; keep warm.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, a little at a time, until lemon colored.
Takes about 5 minutes.
Add to chocolate.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into the chocolate mixture.
Add flavoring. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool, if desired.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt and fruit into whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes (or longer for softer texture) before cutting.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: party chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings at joints, discarding tips.
In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, preserves, green onions, vinegar, oil, Accent and garlic.
Mix well.
Place chicken wings in a shallow baking dish and pour sauce mixture over wings.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove wings from marinade and place single layer on jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil in wok or large pot.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add meat.
Cook until done.
Add salt to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce and early peas.
Cook 1 minute. Add 1/2 cup water.
Add 2 tablespoons sesame oil and add mixture to the cooled rice.
Serve warm.

title: cabbage with caraway
directions: Remove core from the cabbage.
Cut into bite sized pieces. Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Put in cabbage, parsley, sugar, pepper and consomme.
Cover and cook over moderate heat about 12 minutes, basting with the pan juices several times.
About 1 minute before the cabbage is done, sprinkle with caraway seed.
Remove cabbage to a serving dish.
Pour the pan liquid over the cabbage. Yields 6 servings.
Approximate calories per serving:

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 pieces of wax paper and flatten to 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon Italian seasoning on top of each chicken breast.
Place a piece of ham and a piece of cheese on top of this.
Beginning with large end of chicken, roll up and secure with toothpick.
Mix mayonnaise and water.
Dip each breast in mayonnaise mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish prepared with vegetable spray.
Bake at 400° for approximately 25 to 35 minutes or until fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add Wesson oil and beat; add eggs, one at a time, beat after each addition.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in 2 quarts salted water until tender. Drain and rinse well. Drain again. Toss vegetables in with macaroni. Add sour cream, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well, being gentle, then sprinkle with paprika.

title: pink cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in mayo and sugar.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream to which the powdered sugar and vanilla has been added.
Pour into Pyrex pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Freeze 6 hours before serving.

title: pickled squash
directions: Layer vegetables in bowl and sprinkle generously with salt. Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices. Pour over vegetables and bring to boil.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: deer meat "ala clyde"
directions: Roll deer meat in flour and egg batter.
Heat cooking oil. Drop in meat cubes, one at a time, turning until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in onion and bell peppers.
When tender, remove and serve with milk gravy and biscuits.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Generously grease bottom of shallow baking dish with butter or margarine.
Put a sprinkling of crumbs on bottom, then a layer of oysters on top of crumbs.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Microwave or cook bacon or sausage; drain.
Spread potatoes in 9-inch pie plate (microwavable).
Bake, uncovered, on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Combine milk, salt, pepper and eggs.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mom's mandel brot
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; add chips and blend.
On a cookie sheet, make two strips about 3 x 12-inches.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; loosen.
Slice carefully and return to oven.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Place in shallow dish. pour milk over onions.
Soak 30 minutes.
Turn twice.

title: "shrimp crisps"(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Peel zucchini or eggplant.
Cut into slices.
Dip in beaten egg with pepper and a little salt added.
Roll in cracker meal.

title: grandma ava's caramel meringue pie
directions: Caramelize 2/3 cup sugar by melting sugar over low heat without stirring, taking caution not to burn.
Set this aside. Sift
together 1/3 cup of sugar and flour.	Stir in egg yolks. Heat
milk.
Mix
a small amount of warm milk with sugar-flour mixture.
When
milk
is
hot, stir remainder into sugar-flour mixture,
adding
caramelized
sugar.
Stir
until thick.
Add vanilla
and
oleo,
stirring
until well blended.	Put in pie crust and top with meringue.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Put in pan; pat down.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased
and floured 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie crust.
Fry bacon.
Spread cheese and bacon in shell. Mix other ingredients together; pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake until light brown on top.

title: no crust cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325° or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in saucepan soup, mushrooms, almonds and sour cream. Bring to slow boil.

title: marinated cukes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Better if made 8 to 10 hours before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add livers, onions, seasonings and salt.
Cover and cook until tender.
Remove bay leaf and brandy. Cool 10 minutes.
Whirl smooth in blender (or press through coarse sieve).
Pack into oiled mold.
Cover and refrigerate or store in freezer.
Makes 2 cups.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese with cracker crumbs. Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Put a layer of crumbs and cheese in bottom of casserole dish. Add layer of tips and sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with soup and repeat, ending with crackers and cheese on top. Decorate with nuts.
Pour butter over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Separately prepare 1 package each, cherry, orange and lime gelatin, using 1 cup cold water with each.
Turn into shallow square dishes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Scald pineapple juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Prepare 1 envelope unflavored gelatin and 1/4 cup cold water; add to pineapple juice.
Set aside to cool.
Whip 1 pint heavy cream until thick.
Cut firm fruit gelatin into small cubes and fold into whipped cream.
Fold in juice mixture.
Roll 1 box graham crackers to fine crumbs.
Add 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup sugar; mix well.
Press half the crumbs into bottom of buttered pan, reserving spread whipped cream-gelatin mixture over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: orange julies
directions: In blender, blend juice, water, milk and vanilla.
Add ice to fill and blend on high speed until ice is crushed.
You may add honey to sweeten, if needed.
Other juices may be substituted.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain. Mix peas, mushrooms, tuna and soup with noodles. Line baking dish with crushed potato chips.
Add noodles. Top with remaining potato chips and sliced cheese. Heat in oven until cheese has
melted.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
(One 6 ounce roll of jalapeno cheese may be substituted for jalapenos if cheese amount is decreased to 1 cup.)
Stir all ingredients well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: magic finger jello
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1 cup of cold water and set aside.
In a saucepan, bring one cup of water to a boil and add jello.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture.
Stir and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into a lightly greased pan and refrigerate until solid (about 2 hours).
Cut into squares or use a cookie cutter; store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Continue to boil 5 to 7 minutes after it starts.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and marshmallows.
Beat until creamy or starts to get hard.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: hamburger noodle delight
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Stir in noodles and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: calzone
directions: Roll dough into 12-inch circle.
Place filling on one side. Fold in half and seal well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dutch potato filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until brown on top.
May be refrigerated overnight.

title: light pumpkin pancakes
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, in a large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine egg whites, milk, pumpkin and 2 tablespoons oil. Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth until done.
Drain.
Debone chicken and combine with cooked spaghetti; also, add soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes (according to how hot you want it) and Velveeta cheese.
Toss well to mix.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in conventional oven or microwave until cheese on top has melted.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Generously
grease pie pan with butter.
Slice jalapeno peppers (thinly)
in bottom of pan.
Take sharp Cheddar cheese and grate.
Cover peppers with cheese. Beat eggs and pour over the cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Add fresh green pepper or sweet pepper flakes.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
(Puree the tomatoes.)
Add garlic, brown sugar, Italian seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer.
In a large pan, cook the noodles.
Drain when they are done.
Pour sauce over the noodles.
Heat and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add remaining Durkee onions and bake 5 minutes or until browned.

title: strawberry-banana jello(dessert or condiment)
directions: Add Jell-O to boiled water; mix well.
Add frozen strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Mix. Pour half of the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill to firm (about 1/2 hour).
Spread sour cream on top of chilled mixture, then add remaining Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Chill.
(Looks nice in a glass pan or bowl.)

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool cake completely.
Mix frosting and cream cheese together.
Frost cake.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In 2-quart casserole, arrange broccoli; top with chicken and mushrooms.
Combine soup, milk and pepper; pour over chicken. Combine crushed crackers, cheese and paprika; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling. Serves 4.

title: spanglers orange circus peanut gelatin
directions: Cut into small pieces the Spanglers orange circus peanuts. Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Add the pieces of Spanglers circus peanuts stirring until dissolved.
Drain the syrup from the mandarin oranges, adding enough cold water to equal 1 3/4 cup liquid.
Add to gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Stir together the mandarin oranges and whipped topping, fold into the gelatin mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Chill until firm.

title: apple salad
directions: Make sauce from pineapple juice.
Cook 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Can add a sprinkle of cloves or cinnamon if desired.

title: chinese style fried rice
directions: Bring water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook eggs in butter in a 10-inch skillet until set.
Add onion and rice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until rice and onion are lightly browned.
Combine remaining water and soy sauce.
Stir in the rice.

title: hermits
directions: Grease a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add water and eggs. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves and mix into wet ingredients.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Press onto cookie sheet or pan.
Brush with the 2 tablespoons of eggs. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour. Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients until butter melts.
Add sugar, flour and salt to liquid, then add soda, vanilla, sour cream and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut in half lengthwise.

Scoop out seeds. Combine cream cheese and deviled ham; beat until smooth. Spoon into cucumber halves. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Cut each cucumber half in half lengthwise, then cut crosswise into quarters. Chill.
Yields 32 pieces.

title: herbed baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine all ingredients and mix well, then pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: black olive dip
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Blend; chop and chill.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift flour, soda and salt into a large bowl.
Add raisins and nuts.
Toss lightly.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Then add milk.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes on high speed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and celery until tender in water.
Combine ingredients, except the cheese and potato chips.
Place in casserole and bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Place grated cheese on top of casserole and return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place potato chips on top of hot casserole after taking out of oven, so chips won't get too brown.
This keeps well in the freezer.
Delicious.

title: corn pudding
directions: This will work with frozen corn as well.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage (and ham if using) in 4-quart pan.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to sausage with tomatoes, shrimp and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Cook onion in bacon grease until tender, not brown.
Crumble bacon; add onions and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mash to a paste the garlic, croutons and anchovies with a fork in a wooden bowl.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and egg yolk and mix well.
Slowly pour in olive oil and mix while pouring until creamy.
Squeeze the juice of 1 lemon and add dash of red wine vinegar and some grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix all together.

title: garden deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs crosswise in slices.
Scoop yolks out into small bowl; mash well.
Set egg whites aside.
Stir cheese spread, Miracle Whip, mustard and pimentos into yolks until smooth and well blended.
Place egg white slices on wheat bran wafers.
Spoon egg yolk mixture onto egg whites.
Garnish with parsley and tomato.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce and layer with onion, water chestnuts, celery and peas.
Spread with mayonnaise over the top.
Sprinkle with sugar, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Chill 24 hours before serving.
Garnish with 3 hard-boiled eggs, bacon bits and tomato wedges.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and paprika as a finishing touch.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Wash and cook potatoes about halfway in microwave.
Cut in large chunks, leaving skin on.
Mix potatoes with all ingredients, except 1/2 bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir once while baking and put remaining bacon bits on top.

title: candied yam casserole
directions: Cook yams until soft.
Drain into colander.
Put yams back into pot.
Mash with potato masher.
Add orange juice, cinnamon and raisins.
Stir in thoroughly.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until marshmallows are puffed and golden brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix until creamy and bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 325°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place each breast on a sheet of wax paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts into egg mixture and roll each in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in hot oil; drain on paper towels.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain oil from skillet.
Combine tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder in skillet.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in butter.
Pour mixture over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and arrange cheese slices on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add boiling water and stir well. Add cream and stir.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Lower to 350° and bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular casserole
directions: Mix everything together and pour in a 3-quart casserole dish or two smaller dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes uncovered.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: joy's chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil chicken until done, approximately 45 minutes.
Cook stewed tomatoes, bell pepper and onions in saucepan until simmering to almost dry.
Prepare Kraft dinner spaghetti as directed on box.
In a 3-quart micro-dish (Pyrex), prepare following.
Chop chicken, stewed tomato mix and spaghetti in a bowl.
Add tomato sauce, Kraft seasoning, Parmesan cheese and Velveeta cheese, chopped, in bowl.
Cover and microwave for 12 to 20 minutes, depending on unit or until cheese melts.
Great with garlic bread and salad.

title: yogurt dip for fresh fruit
directions: Stir well.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 cup of dip.
Serves 10 to 15 (small to medium size party).

title: broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli until just thawed.
Drain.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover with can of cream of celery soup, undiluted. Layer sliced American cheese over to cover entire dish.
Next, spread dressing prepared according to package directions over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top before baking, if desired.

title: greek easter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the butter or margarine, sugar, egg yolks, brandy and vanilla together thoroughly.
Measure flour by sifting.
Blend flour and baking powder.
Stir into butter mixture; mix well.
Shape dough in small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter. Place cookies on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are set, but not browned.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar and place a whole clove in center of each cookie.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together in large bowl butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together and then add flour, salt and baking soda.
Add quick oats and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top while hot, then remove from cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Saute until onion is golden brown.
Put in crock-pot with all the remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
Stir in sour cream 1 hour before serving.
Serve over hot buttered noodles or rice.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Wash tomatoes and take out core; grind in blender.
Mix tomatoes, sugar and Jell-O in a large saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until it boils.
Continue cooking for about 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars.
Set to cool.
Freezes very well.
Tastes like raspberry jam.

title: stringy cheese loaf
directions: Slice bread almost through.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spread mixture onto each slice.
Wrap in foil. Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Unwrap and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Put in casserole (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cut butter into small pieces. Put on top of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and bake for 1/2 hour at 350° or until light brown and bubbly.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cook in slow cooker 3 to 4 hours. Can cook overnight to take to carry-in noon meal.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 1 cup salad dressing or mayonnaise, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Chill.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes before removing to rack to finishing cooling.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Mix cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings. Dip chicken in oil. Coat with cheese mixture. Put chicken in skillet sprayed with cooking spray. Cook on medium heat 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: swedish cake
directions: Stir sugar and eggs together;
add pineapple with juice and stir.
Add	remaining
ingredients.
Stir
all
together. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: texas grits
directions: Boil grits in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Add more water, if necessary.
Add salt, savory salt, Tabasco sauce, eggs and margarine.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch utility dish that has been greased.
Bake 1 hour in 250° oven.
Good served with ham or chicken.

title: shrimp oliver(microwave)
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic on High for two minutes. Add shrimp, parsley, paprika, Tabasco and pepper.
Cover.
Cook on High for 7 minutes or until shrimp are tender.
Stir once or twice.
Stir in flour, water, wine and salt.
Cook on High for 2 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Serve over medium egg noodles that have been tossed with butter and Parmesan cheese.

title: beef hash
directions: Chop onions and saute until lightly brown.
Add beef, potatoes and meat stock.
Season and cook about 15 minutes.

title: festive fried squash blossoms
directions: In a medium bowl mix flour, baking powder and garlic salt.
In another bowl combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Dip blossoms into batter (after rinsing). Heat 2 inches of oil in skillet to 375° and fry a few at a time until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm until serving time.

title: hush puppies
directions: Put onion in a blender and blend onion small.
Drain well. Mix other ingredients well.
Mixture should form a soft, but formed ball.
Drop in heated oil and cook for about 2 minutes or until golden brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll and shape rolls to form crust.
Brown sausage; drain and crumble on crust.
Spread hash browns and cheese over sausage. Beat eggs, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour on top of potatoes and cheese.
Bake at 375° until crust is done.

title: microwave 5-minute fudge
directions: In a medium size casserole dish, combine Toll House morsels, condensed milk and butter.
Microwave on High 3 minutes. Turn dish 1/4 turn. Continue microwaving 2 minutes.
Add nuts. Refrigerate 24 hours. Cut and serve.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Cut meat into bite size portions and lay on top of foil.
Sprinkle meat with onion soup mix.
Cut up tomatoes and place on top.
Add peppers and mushrooms.

Mix cornstarch, A.1. sauce and seasonings with reserved tomato liquid and pour over meat and vegetables. Seal foil tightly (to prevent leaks) and bake at 350° for 2 hours. No peeking! It makes its own gravy.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: potato rolls
directions: *Not too much (soft and sticky dough).

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake in muffin cups for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian broccoli soup
directions: Cook the broccoli in the cup of water (don't drain).
Add the remaining ingredients and cook on low until heated and thickened.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar (little bit at a time).
Add eggs one at a time; beat well in between.
Add milk and flour; alternate milk and flour (let milk be last).
Add nuts (fold in). Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: black bottom cups
directions: You will need cupcake holders.
